contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:47.355 --> 01:49.482
Always remember your promise to me.

01:49.470 --> 01:52.640
Never let nobody or nothing
turn you into no cripple.

02:14.537 --> 02:15.663
All right!

02:15.746 --> 02:17.289
Rest stop, 45 minutes.

02:17.414 --> 02:19.667
Come on, folks. We gotta move.

02:19.917 --> 02:23.003
We leave at 2:45 p.m.
On the dot. Can't be late.

02:24.004 --> 02:26.215
Hot meals and bathrooms inside.

02:27.091 --> 02:29.051
All right, uh, there's a
window out back ...

02:29.134 --> 02:30.511
for y'all to buy sandwiches.

02:30.594 --> 02:33.097
And I suggest you make
good use of them outhouses.

02:33.180 --> 02:35.599
Ain't nothing but bushes
for you in the Carolinas.

02:35.641 --> 02:36.892
Sir.

02:39.436 --> 02:40.896
Can I help you, sir?

02:40.938 --> 02:42.064
Yes, sir.

02:43.357 --> 02:44.567
Seattle?

02:45.943 --> 02:47.236
Who you riding with?

02:47.278 --> 02:48.904
Nobody. Just me.

02:49.029 --> 02:51.574
Boy, I can't take responsibility ...

02:51.615 --> 02:54.493
for some blind nigger
traveling 3,500 miles alone.

02:54.577 --> 02:56.745
I ... I ... I paid for this here
ticket, and it says ...

02:56.829 --> 02:58.873
that you have to take me
to Seattle.

02:59.039 --> 03:01.584
Don't you be smarting off
to me, boy.

03:02.459 --> 03:04.712
With all due respect, sir,
I believe I earned the right.

03:04.795 --> 03:06.672
I may have left my eyes
on Omaha Beach,

03:06.755 --> 03:08.841
but I ain't asking no charity
from Uncle Sam.

03:08.924 --> 03:11.176
I got a job waiting
for me in Seattle.

03:12.636 --> 03:13.846
You were in Normandy?

03:13.929 --> 03:16.223
Shuttling troopers to the beach.

03:16.682 --> 03:18.475
We took a direct hit.

03:23.606 --> 03:24.982
I'm sorry, son.

03:26.734 --> 03:28.777
I'll keep an eye on you myself.

03:28.861 --> 03:31.196
Come on. Take a seat in the back.

03:38.621 --> 03:41.415
♪ Any time ♪

03:41.665 --> 03:45.461
♪ You're feeling lonely ♪

03:45.586 --> 03:48.505
♪ Anytime ♪

03:48.547 --> 03:50.799
♪ You're feeling blue ♪

03:52.384 --> 03:55.137
♪ Anytime ♪

03:55.346 --> 03:58.349
♪ Anytime you feel down hearted ♪

03:59.266 --> 04:03.979
♪ That will prove
your love for me is true ♪

04:04.021 --> 04:05.606
♪ Anytime ♪

04:05.856 --> 04:08.984
♪ You're thinkin' about me ♪

04:15.282 --> 04:17.535
Til, what the hell
do you think you're doin'?

04:17.618 --> 04:19.620
Billy, don't get
your feathers all ruffled now.

04:19.702 --> 04:22.414
I met this ol' boy over
at the O.C. At Clarkfield,

04:22.498 --> 04:24.083
and well, he plays
a mean jazz piano.

04:24.166 --> 04:26.460
I don't care if he whistles
Dixie out his ass.

04:26.544 --> 04:28.504
He ain't gonna do it here.

04:28.546 --> 04:29.880
Sir.

04:30.130 --> 04:31.882
Boy, are you blind?

04:31.966 --> 04:33.592
Yes, sir. Since I was seven.

04:35.386 --> 04:37.054
Well, let me help you out then.

04:37.137 --> 04:39.265
This is a country band.

04:39.390 --> 04:41.642
We don't play no boogie-woogie.

04:41.892 --> 04:44.270
Uh, yes, I understand.
I love country music.

04:44.353 --> 04:46.855
All right, go on. Tell me.

04:46.939 --> 04:49.400
What is it you love
about country music?

04:49.483 --> 04:50.776
I ... I love the stories.

04:50.859 --> 04:52.403
Uh, you know,
about fallin' in love ...

04:52.486 --> 04:54.154
and having love
knock you around ...

04:54.238 --> 04:56.198
and then the pressures
of the world on you so tough.

04:56.282 --> 04:57.533
It ... It makes you
feel small.

04:57.575 --> 04:59.034
You want to give your soul to God.

04:59.076 --> 05:01.078
You might as well.
Your ass belongs to Him.

05:10.170 --> 05:11.630
Boy, are you sure you blind?

05:11.714 --> 05:13.090
Last time I checked.

05:26.186 --> 05:27.646
Okay. Come on in.

05:41.785 --> 05:44.246
Billy, I think you're outvoted.

05:44.580 --> 05:46.707
Til, one hint of trouble,

05:46.790 --> 05:48.584
and your blind nigra's out of here.

05:50.461 --> 05:51.545
Damn!

05:52.171 --> 05:53.255
Here.

05:53.422 --> 05:55.925
I'm gonna have
to put some glasses

05:55.966 --> 05:58.594
before he scares
somebody half to death.

06:08.395 --> 06:10.147
Seattle, Washington, folks.

06:10.231 --> 06:12.233
Change bus here
for all points north:

06:12.316 --> 06:13.943
Bellingham, Mount Vernon.

06:13.984 --> 06:15.653
Vancouver, Canada.

06:34.296 --> 06:36.549
Uh, that's Diz. Emanon.

06:37.508 --> 06:39.385
Yeah. But what's it
spell backwards?

06:39.468 --> 06:40.719
Ah ... ah ... ah, come on, man.

06:40.803 --> 06:43.013
Why don't you give me
something difficult?

06:43.097 --> 06:44.348
"No Name."

06:45.849 --> 06:47.935
Say, daddy-o, what ax you play?

06:48.018 --> 06:48.978
Uh, piano.

06:49.019 --> 06:50.396
Just blew in from Tampa, Florida.

06:50.479 --> 06:52.314
Me and my partner,
Gossie McGee, came here,

06:52.398 --> 06:54.024
you know, want to
fatten up our style.

06:54.108 --> 06:56.402
Cop some licks from some more
experienced cats. You dig?

06:56.485 --> 06:57.653
You know what?

06:57.736 --> 06:59.321
Why don't you let me
take you inside?

06:59.405 --> 07:00.531
You know, show you around.

07:00.614 --> 07:02.157
- All right.
- Perfect gentleman.
- Yeah.

07:02.241 --> 07:03.701
This is just like my place.

07:03.784 --> 07:04.994
So, what's your name?

07:05.035 --> 07:06.120
Ray Robinson.

07:06.203 --> 07:07.246
I'm Quincy Jones.

07:07.329 --> 07:08.289
Quincy Jones.

07:08.372 --> 07:10.666
Hey, Gerry!
This here's my man, Ray.

07:10.749 --> 07:12.501
He's here to see his friend,
Gossie McGee.

07:12.585 --> 07:14.086
So I figured
I'll show him inside ...

07:14.169 --> 07:16.338
Don't mess with me, Q.
He can come in, but not you.

07:16.422 --> 07:18.883
Vice is on my ass for letting
you underage kids in.

07:18.924 --> 07:20.092
Get out of here, Q.

07:20.175 --> 07:21.635
- Can't you see ...
- Get out of here, Q.

07:21.719 --> 07:23.512
- He's blind! I gotta show him in.
- Get out.

07:23.554 --> 07:25.347
- Jive-ass.
- What?

07:25.431 --> 07:28.183
Hey, Ray Robinson, when am I
gonna hear you play, baby?

07:28.225 --> 07:29.852
Uh, well, that may cost you.

07:30.603 --> 07:35.399
Welcome, all you cool cats
and fine felines.

07:35.482 --> 07:38.402
You've come to the place where
the sophisti-cats and hipsters ...

07:38.485 --> 07:40.362
hang their bebop hats.

07:40.529 --> 07:42.698
So snuggle up and come near ...

07:42.781 --> 07:44.366
for tonight is Talent Night
at The Rocking Chair.

07:46.785 --> 07:49.830
Let's hear it for "Dancin' Al!"

07:59.423 --> 08:02.760
Gossie's been cattin' around with one
of my waitresses since he got here.

08:02.843 --> 08:05.971
He never told me that his partner
was a blind 'Bama boy.

08:06.180 --> 08:08.474
Marlene, Demurs just called.

08:08.557 --> 08:10.434
Thurmond's sick.

08:10.684 --> 08:11.936
What about Sassy?

08:12.019 --> 08:13.229
Flat tire.

08:20.736 --> 08:24.240
Okay, 'Bama. Why don't you get on
up there and show me what you got?

08:24.406 --> 08:27.326
Well, I — I'm not prepared to do
my thing right now, tonight ...

08:27.409 --> 08:29.578
This is the only audition
you're going to get, puddin'.

08:29.620 --> 08:33.207
So either get on up there, or you and
Gossie can haul your asses back down South.

08:33.289 --> 08:35.208
Here. Smoke some of this.

08:39.129 --> 08:40.756
This ain't no tobacco, man.

08:40.839 --> 08:42.716
No, hold it in,
it'll calm you down.

08:42.799 --> 08:44.134
All right, Oberon.

08:44.217 --> 08:45.678
Get on up there and introduce him.

08:45.761 --> 08:47.137
Yes, ma'am.

08:47.596 --> 08:49.974
Okay, 'Bama. Let's go.

08:51.308 --> 08:52.518
Yeah.

08:55.104 --> 08:59.400
Now, I got something special
for all you satin dolls.

08:59.483 --> 09:02.194
And I don't mean
Oberon's big thunder.

09:03.404 --> 09:05.114
Now that's for another show.

09:05.155 --> 09:07.408
Now we got some new blood for ya.

09:07.491 --> 09:09.618
Yeah, straight off
the bus from Florida,

09:09.660 --> 09:14.498
I give you Ray
"Don't Call Me Sugar" Robinson!

09:23.924 --> 09:25.217
How y'all doing tonight?

09:25.301 --> 09:26.510
Better than you!

09:29.513 --> 09:30.764
Relax, Ray. Relax.

09:30.848 --> 09:31.974
I got it.

09:38.022 --> 09:39.523
Uh-uh, what do y'all want to hear?

09:41.859 --> 09:43.736
How about a little Nat King Cole?

09:50.242 --> 09:52.161
Y'all like Nat King Cole?

09:55.206 --> 09:59.460
♪ If you ever plan to travel west ♪

10:01.128 --> 10:02.379
'Bama ain't bad.

10:02.463 --> 10:04.215
Yeah, I'd say he saved our asses.

10:06.717 --> 10:08.510
What the hell is
Ray doin' up there?

10:08.677 --> 10:10.512
Auditioning for you, Gossie.

10:11.096 --> 10:13.057
He ain't no good without me.

10:14.058 --> 10:17.019
How'd you and the 'Bama like to
do a week here at the Chair?

10:17.061 --> 10:18.479
I know a good bass player.

10:18.562 --> 10:21.857
A nice jazz trio could score
big with the right manager.

10:22.733 --> 10:23.901
Manager?

10:24.568 --> 10:26.654
Come on now, Gossie,
don't be so small-minded.

10:26.737 --> 10:28.280
You know you've got to give to get.

10:28.364 --> 10:30.366
Now what exactly do I have to give?

10:30.407 --> 10:31.784
25 percent.

10:31.867 --> 10:33.369
But I'll be gettin' you other gigs.

10:33.452 --> 10:36.372
All right,
next question: What do I get?

10:37.081 --> 10:38.374
What do you need?

10:38.457 --> 10:41.377
Double scale as leader,
plus 10 percent.

10:42.753 --> 10:44.046
What about the 'Bama?

10:44.088 --> 10:46.590
He's about as green
as a blade of grass.

10:47.424 --> 10:48.717
I can handle him.

10:48.759 --> 10:50.386
♪ Flagstaff, Arizona ♪

10:50.928 --> 10:52.096
Yeah, he's green.

10:52.179 --> 10:53.639
♪ Kingman, Barstow ♪

10:53.722 --> 10:55.474
So, Gossie,
you don't need to worry ...

10:55.558 --> 10:57.059
about a hotel room for the 'Bama.

10:57.393 --> 10:59.144
He can flop at my place.

11:00.187 --> 11:01.814
Hey, y'all never change.

11:01.897 --> 11:05.901
♪ Get your kicks on Route sixty-six ♪

11:09.113 --> 11:11.407
Ray, you coming back to bed?

11:12.950 --> 11:14.326
I'm getting some water.

11:14.410 --> 11:17.288
I can see that,
but mama ain't finished yet.

11:17.955 --> 11:19.748
For the first time anywhere,

11:19.790 --> 11:22.793
let's hear it for "The McSon Trio!"

11:22.835 --> 11:25.462
♪ A buzzard took the monkey
for a ride in the air ♪

11:25.546 --> 11:28.632
♪ The monkey thought that
everything was on the square ♪

11:28.716 --> 11:30.175
Ray, when you coming out?

11:30.259 --> 11:31.510
In a minute.

11:32.052 --> 11:35.472
Mama's got some more blackberry
cobbler for you, baby.

11:36.098 --> 11:37.224
Damn.

11:38.976 --> 11:41.312
♪ Straighten up and fly right ♪

11:41.395 --> 11:43.939
♪ Cool down, papa,
don't you blow your top ♪

11:52.990 --> 11:55.075
Marlene, if you're gonna
send us out on tour,

11:55.159 --> 11:56.744
we're gonna need
more than $5 a day.

11:56.827 --> 11:58.871
How come we can't get paid
after each gig?

11:58.954 --> 12:01.123
Because you boys will spend
everything you make.

12:01.165 --> 12:04.084
The club sends the checks
to me, so as I can bank them.

12:04.168 --> 12:06.545
I just want to see
my own checks, that's all.

12:06.629 --> 12:09.506
You don't see, Ray.
You're blind, baby.

12:09.548 --> 12:11.258
Or did you forget?

12:11.884 --> 12:15.346
Now, you want to go out on your
own and see how well you do?

12:23.395 --> 12:26.148
Ray! Hey, Marlene, where's Ray?

12:26.190 --> 12:29.151
He's in the back bedroom.
And wipe your feet.

12:34.823 --> 12:38.827
Ray, uh, six-nine, where you at?
Six-nine. Six-nine.

12:40.079 --> 12:42.498
Lionel Hampton just asked me
to go on the road with him, man!

12:42.540 --> 12:44.124
Lionel Hampton, man!

12:44.208 --> 12:46.001
- Sure he did.
- Then why you still here?

12:46.085 --> 12:50.047
And dig this: His wife, she
kicked me off the tour bus.

12:50.130 --> 12:52.967
Told me to come back when I
started shaving. You believe that?

12:53.050 --> 12:56.178
Uh ... uh, Seven-oh, could you do me a
favor, man, and close that bag for me?

12:56.220 --> 12:58.556
What's wrong? You got two hands.
You can close it yourself.

12:58.639 --> 13:00.391
I got two feet, too.
Could you close it?

13:00.474 --> 13:02.059
I got it.

13:04.061 --> 13:05.688
Excuse me, sir!

13:07.106 --> 13:09.275
Man, we're gonna be late.

13:09.733 --> 13:12.027
I got to get my own place, Gossie.

13:12.695 --> 13:16.031
Why? I mean,
you got free rent right now.

13:16.240 --> 13:18.200
Like hell it's free rent.

13:22.329 --> 13:23.539
Oh, come on, Ray.

13:23.622 --> 13:25.541
Why you gonna mess
with a good thing?

13:25.583 --> 13:27.877
All I'm saying is you keep
layin' that pipe with Marlene,

13:27.960 --> 13:29.920
and I bet you she's gonna
make us all rich.

13:29.962 --> 13:31.797
Hey, sir, excuse me!

13:38.387 --> 13:39.889
♪ Straighten up and fly right ♪

13:40.806 --> 13:43.058
♪ Straighten up and stay right ♪

13:43.350 --> 13:45.686
♪ Straighten up and fly right ♪

13:45.769 --> 13:46.937
♪ Cool down, papa ♪

13:47.021 --> 13:51.901
♪ Don't you blow your top ♪

13:58.949 --> 14:00.951
Just back from their
triumphant tour ...

14:01.035 --> 14:04.455
of the Yakima Valley,
The McSon Trio!

14:04.622 --> 14:06.081
They'll be back right here,

14:06.165 --> 14:08.417
same time, same place, next week.

14:12.463 --> 14:16.258
Hey, baby, you sound more like
Nat than the King himself.

14:18.135 --> 14:19.220
What's your name?

14:19.303 --> 14:20.304
Ray Robinson.

14:20.512 --> 14:21.680
Ray Robinson?

14:21.764 --> 14:24.266
I'm Jack Lauderdale,
Swing Time Records.

14:24.350 --> 14:27.311
Oh, hey ... hey, hey, Jack!
How you doing, man?

14:27.353 --> 14:28.562
Good. Oh, good.

14:28.646 --> 14:30.272
How about us makin'
a record together?

14:30.314 --> 14:32.399
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Hell, yeah! Let's do that.

14:32.483 --> 14:33.651
Can I help you?

14:33.734 --> 14:34.777
I don't think so.

14:34.818 --> 14:37.112
We're just talking
a little business.

14:37.196 --> 14:40.366
Then you need to talk to me,
'cause I'm his manager.

14:40.783 --> 14:42.159
Whichever way the wind blows.

14:42.243 --> 14:43.369
It's blowing.

14:43.452 --> 14:44.995
Jack Lauderdale,
Swing Time Records.

14:45.079 --> 14:46.956
- Marlene Andres.
- Marlene?

14:46.997 --> 14:48.499
- Gossie McGee.
- Gossie McGee.

14:48.582 --> 14:49.792
Great set, baby.

14:49.833 --> 14:51.835
We're going to talk
with Mr. Lauderdale here.

14:51.877 --> 14:53.212
Come on, Jack. I'm buying.

14:53.295 --> 14:54.713
I'm coming in, uh, to talk to him.

14:54.797 --> 14:56.840
You are doing a fabulous job!

14:56.924 --> 14:57.967
Yes, man.

14:58.008 --> 15:00.010
Eh, look, let's talk to him
about this record.

15:00.094 --> 15:02.179
Hey, no, no, we're gonna
let Marlene handle that.

15:02.263 --> 15:04.181
You get Oberon
to call you a cab, all right.

15:04.265 --> 15:05.808
Great set, Ray.

15:06.934 --> 15:08.143
Goss!

15:08.185 --> 15:10.312
Hey, daddy-o, want a smoke?

15:10.854 --> 15:12.856
I got some gage, fresh off the boat.

15:12.898 --> 15:14.358
It's clean and seedless.

15:14.441 --> 15:16.193
So that's how it is, huh?

15:16.402 --> 15:19.196
You keep me high
while they talk the business?

15:19.363 --> 15:21.073
I ain't the one playing you, man.

15:24.201 --> 15:25.494
Oberon, listen ...

15:25.786 --> 15:29.164
You know, Marlene and Gossie are the
ones running the game on you, Ray.

15:29.206 --> 15:30.291
What?

15:30.374 --> 15:32.877
They sliced up the pie
the first night you played.

15:32.960 --> 15:34.670
35 percent off the top.

15:34.753 --> 15:36.797
Plus Gossie's
double scale as leader.

15:37.214 --> 15:38.507
Leader?
If anybody's leading the band,

15:38.549 --> 15:40.759
I'm the one that's the leader.

15:41.051 --> 15:42.595
Forget the bo' humps.
You know what?

15:42.678 --> 15:44.013
I ... I'm ... I'm gonna go
my own way.

15:44.096 --> 15:45.973
Who's gonna book your gigs?

15:46.098 --> 15:48.017
Marlene's got you locked up.

15:48.058 --> 15:50.853
And she ain't gonna give up
her golden goose.

15:50.978 --> 15:53.689
♪ Straighten up and fly right ♪

15:53.731 --> 15:56.275
♪ Cool down, papa,
don't you blow your top ♪

15:56.358 --> 15:58.527
Hey, Ray Robinson,
you are fantastic.

15:59.445 --> 16:01.739
There you go. Give me some skin.

16:03.365 --> 16:04.450
What's that?

16:04.533 --> 16:05.701
Jack's card.

16:05.784 --> 16:07.870
I got his number at the hotel.

16:13.709 --> 16:15.669
Come on, Q.
It's not that complicated.

16:15.753 --> 16:17.046
Now let's just play it again.

16:17.129 --> 16:18.964
That's a B flat, C 7, scale it up,

16:19.048 --> 16:20.966
and triple it off the back end.

16:23.260 --> 16:25.429
Yeah, nigger! Yeah, that's it.

16:26.972 --> 16:30.059
Ray, what did I tell you
about cookin' in the dark?

16:30.100 --> 16:31.769
Are you tryin'
to burn the house down?

16:31.852 --> 16:34.396
Think about it, Marlene. Uh ... uh,
what do I need the light for?

16:34.438 --> 16:36.232
Well, you don't need
to be cookin' anyway.

16:36.273 --> 16:37.858
We brought you
takeout from Oscar's.

16:37.942 --> 16:38.984
Well, get your money back.

16:39.068 --> 16:40.402
I got fried chicken right here.

16:40.486 --> 16:41.779
Come on, Seven-oh, try this.

16:41.862 --> 16:43.364
Yeah! About time.

16:45.199 --> 16:47.034
Hey, that's home-cooked,
right there.

16:47.117 --> 16:48.244
Mmm, no, thank you.

16:48.327 --> 16:49.745
This chicken is the mostest, huh.

16:49.787 --> 16:52.081
Just needs a little hot sauce
and it'll be perfect.

16:52.122 --> 16:54.166
Yeah. So, what did
Jack Lauderdale have to say?

16:54.250 --> 16:55.834
Oh, I clocked him
comin' out the gate.

16:55.918 --> 16:57.169
He's a two-bit hustler.

16:57.253 --> 16:58.420
Oh, I see.

16:58.462 --> 17:01.006
Yeah, turns out the only hit
that Swing Time ever had ...

17:01.090 --> 17:03.259
was Open the Door, Richard,
which was a joke record.

17:03.342 --> 17:05.219
Uh ... uh ... uh, what about him
recordin' me?

17:05.301 --> 17:07.637
Oh, he'll record you,
if we pay the freight.

17:07.805 --> 17:09.431
Scratch a liar, find a thief.

17:10.558 --> 17:12.059
What's that supposed to mean?

17:12.142 --> 17:13.352
This.

17:14.103 --> 17:15.980
You see I saw
Jack Lauderdale tonight,

17:16.063 --> 17:18.107
and he gave me a $500
advance on my record.

17:18.147 --> 17:20.442
He also said he'll put me
on the road with Lowell Fulson ...

17:20.483 --> 17:22.027
and pay me three times
what you pay.

17:22.111 --> 17:23.237
Now, that's a lie!

17:23.319 --> 17:26.740
Hey, no way he's not gonna put some
blind man on the road. Think about it.

17:26.824 --> 17:28.742
I mean, you ... you need
watchin' out for.

17:28.826 --> 17:31.036
And he ain't got the time to
look after you the way I do.

17:31.120 --> 17:33.539
Is that what you've been doing,
Gossie? Watchin' out for me?

17:33.622 --> 17:35.457
Is that why you get
paid double what I do?

17:37.001 --> 17:38.168
Who told you that?

17:38.252 --> 17:39.295
It's true, ain't it?

17:39.378 --> 17:41.380
You two have been
gaming me since I got here.

17:41.463 --> 17:43.424
Ray, baby, listen ...
I ain't listening to you!

17:43.507 --> 17:45.885
Ray, I've ... I've been meaning
to talk to you about that.

17:45.968 --> 17:48.012
Then why aren't you talkin'?

17:50.389 --> 17:52.641
Um, look, Ray, Ray,
let's not do nothin' stupid.

17:52.683 --> 17:54.476
I might be blind,
but I ain't stupid!

17:54.518 --> 17:56.228
Q., get my bag from upstairs.

17:56.312 --> 17:57.438
- What?
- Get it!

17:57.521 --> 17:58.981
- Wha ... right now?
- Now.

17:59.064 --> 18:01.317
Ray, man, we done been
through a whole lot.

18:01.358 --> 18:04.111
Ray, now wait a minute.
I can explain everything.

18:04.403 --> 18:06.113
Think about what you're doing.

18:06.197 --> 18:08.032
Ray, Ray, now you're makin'
a big mistake.

18:08.115 --> 18:10.117
That clown is spoutin'
promises that he can't keep.

18:10.201 --> 18:11.952
You'd be a fool to follow him.

18:12.036 --> 18:13.329
Ray, Ray, we'll make a new deal!

18:13.412 --> 18:14.538
Whatever makes you happy!

18:14.622 --> 18:16.540
The deal is
you can lay the pipe now.

18:16.624 --> 18:20.044
You'll break your neck going down
these stairs by yourself. Hang on.

18:20.502 --> 18:21.545
Oh, man.

18:21.629 --> 18:25.382
Ray, I ain't never seen you do
nothing like that, man. Never.

18:25.466 --> 18:27.176
That ain't nothing, Seven-oh.

18:40.147 --> 18:41.982
Stop cheating, Ray.

18:42.816 --> 18:45.444
George, you can't catch me.
Come on.

18:45.528 --> 18:46.862
Aretha!

18:47.571 --> 18:48.864
Come on, George.

18:48.948 --> 18:51.450
Aretha Robinson,
have you lost your mind?

18:51.534 --> 18:54.828
Eula, you promised to split every
wash basket with me, fair and square!

18:54.912 --> 18:55.996
And I did!

18:56.080 --> 18:57.164
Hell, you did!

18:57.248 --> 18:59.333
You charge white folks
one thing and pay me another.

18:59.416 --> 19:00.834
Now who's gonna wash these?

19:00.918 --> 19:02.378
You can. Now pay me my money!

19:05.965 --> 19:07.967
Okay, I'm a-giving you
your two little dollars.

19:08.050 --> 19:10.177
But don't you be expectin'
no more work out of me!

19:10.261 --> 19:11.679
I got all I need out of you.

19:11.804 --> 19:13.264
Ray and George, come on!

19:13.305 --> 19:14.932
That's right.
Get out of my yard ...

19:15.015 --> 19:16.767
and don't y'all never come back!

19:19.687 --> 19:22.439
Y'all got to learn
to read and write real good,

19:22.523 --> 19:25.276
so you never have to work
for people like that.

19:25.359 --> 19:27.069
Scratch a liar, find a thief.

19:27.111 --> 19:28.112
Understand?

19:28.153 --> 19:29.321
Yes, Mama.

19:42.293 --> 19:44.920
Smell that, Ray.
Smell the success.

19:45.212 --> 19:46.630
We're in LA, man,

19:46.672 --> 19:48.966
the place where the Negro
comes to spread his wings.

19:49.049 --> 19:51.468
You ... you know, man, I know
my ears ain't deceivin' me.

19:51.510 --> 19:52.553
Is that Art Tatum?

19:52.636 --> 19:54.263
It sure is, baby.
You want to meet him?

19:54.346 --> 19:57.016
I ... I can't meet him.
A-Art Tatum is the most.

20:02.271 --> 20:06.734
So, Ray, we got to talk about
your name, man: Robinson.

20:06.817 --> 20:09.695
Sugar Ray got the Robinson
franchise all sewed up.

20:09.778 --> 20:13.449
So I'm thinkin' we go with
your middle name, Charles.

20:13.991 --> 20:15.367
As in, Ray Charles.

20:15.451 --> 20:17.161
I don't care
what you call me, man,

20:17.244 --> 20:19.038
just as long as my name's
on the record.

20:19.121 --> 20:20.497
But we're gonna toast to that.

20:20.581 --> 20:21.874
Hey, what's the haps, Jack?

20:21.957 --> 20:23.584
Oh, my goodness.
Give me some skin.

20:23.667 --> 20:25.711
What's up, baby?
How you doin'?

20:25.794 --> 20:29.381
Lowell Fulson, meet your new
piano player: Ray Charles.

20:29.465 --> 20:32.009
Ray Charles, the blind sensation.

20:32.092 --> 20:35.888
Ow! Damn! I'm gonna use that
on the album cover.

20:35.971 --> 20:37.389
He's really the sensation.

20:37.473 --> 20:39.308
I ... I love your music,
Mr. Fulson.

20:39.350 --> 20:40.768
Uh, the man's got taste.

20:40.851 --> 20:43.145
Hey, and the man ain't
been on the road ...

20:43.187 --> 20:45.439
with a band before,
so now you take care of him.

20:45.522 --> 20:46.857
Like my own brother.

20:50.444 --> 20:51.695
Ray.

20:52.571 --> 20:53.697
I'm gonna be right back.

20:53.781 --> 20:54.823
All right.

20:55.366 --> 20:57.993
Yeah, you got the one
on the left.

20:58.035 --> 20:59.828
Look here,
let me do the talking.

21:28.649 --> 21:30.150
Don't go inside that place.

21:30.234 --> 21:31.694
You know what Mama said.

21:31.735 --> 21:34.238
Go home
and don't tell Mama nothin'.

21:34.738 --> 21:36.115
Go, George.

21:40.578 --> 21:42.413
George, get out of here!

22:08.188 --> 22:11.025
Hey, boy, who let you in?

22:11.275 --> 22:13.402
You must be Aretha's son, huh?

22:13.444 --> 22:15.696
Yes, sir. Ray Charles Robinson.

22:16.155 --> 22:18.908
I've been seeing you
sneakin' around here.

22:19.241 --> 22:20.910
You like the piano, huh?

22:21.493 --> 22:23.537
Come on, you want
to learn how to play?

22:23.621 --> 22:24.914
Come on over here.

22:24.955 --> 22:26.707
Let me show you how to play.
Come on.

22:26.790 --> 22:29.001
I'm gonna teach you how to play.

22:29.084 --> 22:32.004
What we'll do, I'm gonna teach
you three notes, right?

22:32.087 --> 22:34.173
This is the first note,
right here.

22:35.758 --> 22:36.842
Play that.

22:38.135 --> 22:40.346
And here's the second note,
right here.

22:41.513 --> 22:42.765
Play that.

22:44.475 --> 22:46.101
Here's the third note.

22:49.146 --> 22:50.439
Now, here's the way it goes.

22:50.522 --> 22:52.107
Listen. Listen closely, now.

22:55.861 --> 22:57.196
Play that.

22:58.781 --> 23:00.115
Good!

23:01.283 --> 23:03.035
Try the other notes.

23:11.877 --> 23:13.337
Every club we hit,

23:13.420 --> 23:15.881
it's your responsibility
to rehearse the band.

23:16.006 --> 23:18.008
These are some lazy-ass bastards,

23:18.092 --> 23:20.386
so you gotta make sure
that they don't slough off.

23:20.803 --> 23:22.930
You gotta be ready
and dressed to open the show.

23:23.013 --> 23:25.349
Now, Lowell likes to take
a nap before he goes on.

23:25.432 --> 23:28.477
You just do your thing
until he feels like comin' out.

23:28.561 --> 23:31.480
And when Lowell's playin',
you keep the band sharp.

23:31.522 --> 23:32.523
Uh ... uh, just one thing.

23:32.606 --> 23:33.524
What?

23:33.607 --> 23:35.734
Did Jack tell you that
I have to be paid in singles?

23:36.863 --> 23:39.247
You just do your job,
you're gonna get your money.

23:39.989 --> 23:41.657
♪ Baby, come on, down ♪

23:41.699 --> 23:44.869
♪ Your daddy's
in the heart of town ♪

23:48.622 --> 23:50.124
♪ Come on down ♪

23:50.207 --> 23:53.627
♪ Your daddy's in the heart of town ♪

23:59.884 --> 24:02.219
How'd you get the name
Fathead anyway?

24:02.303 --> 24:03.804
Why do they call me Fathead?

24:03.929 --> 24:05.472
Nah, you don't want to hear.

24:05.556 --> 24:07.516
But this is what
I really want to know.

24:07.600 --> 24:09.685
Do any of you
fine young ladies know ...

24:09.727 --> 24:12.104
where we can get a nice steak
this time of night?

24:12.187 --> 24:15.191
You mean something big,
thick, and juicy?

24:15.274 --> 24:17.067
Oh, yeah, that's just what I mean.

24:18.319 --> 24:20.571
Fathead, where you guys
headed, man?

24:21.155 --> 24:23.240
I ain't babysittin' no blind cat.

24:24.241 --> 24:25.659
Uh, I'm sorry, Ray,

24:25.743 --> 24:28.454
but, uh, the law says
there's only six to a cab.

24:28.537 --> 24:30.539
Come on, ladies,
let's get out of here.

25:27.304 --> 25:29.473
♪ Everyday ♪

25:34.645 --> 25:38.315
♪ Everyday I have the blues ♪

25:44.822 --> 25:48.158
♪ Everyday, everyday ♪

25:52.496 --> 25:54.790
Pay up, baby!
Yeah, that's all right.

25:54.832 --> 25:57.126
I been shootin' craps
since I was 12 years old.

25:57.167 --> 25:59.753
Don't never shoot craps
on a white woman's grave.

25:59.837 --> 26:00.796
Why not?

26:00.880 --> 26:01.964
It's bad luck.

26:02.006 --> 26:05.426
♪ You know bad luck
and trouble, people ♪

26:08.804 --> 26:11.473
♪ Well, you know I had my share ♪

26:17.771 --> 26:19.481
That's for being late to the bus.

26:19.523 --> 26:21.025
Wilbur, you a low-down piece ...

26:21.108 --> 26:22.568
You better move on.

26:28.032 --> 26:30.201
Ah, Mr. One-dollar Bill.

26:31.243 --> 26:34.914
$5, $10, $15, $20 ...

26:36.040 --> 26:38.667
Now, you like to start
counting that again?

26:39.877 --> 26:41.712
All right, damn you.

26:44.048 --> 26:46.217
$284, $285 ...

26:46.300 --> 26:49.136
Listen, man, I ain't
no damn seein'-eye dog.

26:49.220 --> 26:52.640
♪ You know ain't nobody worried
about me ♪

26:54.225 --> 26:58.896
♪ I don't see nobody, nobody cryin' ♪

27:05.903 --> 27:08.364
Fathead, open up. Open up.
I got to take a leak.

27:11.367 --> 27:14.161
Hey, what you doing, man?
Close the door, Fat!

27:14.411 --> 27:16.705
Say, Ray, we'll be in here
for a little while.

27:16.747 --> 27:19.542
Use the women's can,
down there on your right.

27:19.625 --> 27:21.168
I don't want to use
the women's can.

27:21.252 --> 27:22.294
This way, alright.

27:42.106 --> 27:43.399
Oh, God!

27:44.358 --> 27:46.235
Say, Ray, you all right?

27:47.403 --> 27:49.113
Yeah, I must have slipped
on the wet.

27:49.196 --> 27:50.281
There's a pipe broke.

27:50.364 --> 27:51.907
There's water everywhere.
You see it?

27:51.991 --> 27:53.909
Let's go, man. Close the door.

27:53.951 --> 27:55.369
All right, quit playing, Ray.

27:55.452 --> 27:57.913
We'll be in here a while.
Now go on now!

28:05.629 --> 28:06.672
Where you from, Ray?

28:06.755 --> 28:07.965
North Florida.

28:08.382 --> 28:09.884
Oh, North Florida boy.

28:10.426 --> 28:11.594
Your people still down there?

28:11.719 --> 28:12.887
No.

28:14.096 --> 28:15.222
All right.

28:15.723 --> 28:17.224
Hey, uh, pardon me for askin',

28:17.308 --> 28:19.226
but how do you
get around so good ...

28:19.310 --> 28:21.186
without a cane or a dog?

28:21.979 --> 28:24.857
How do you get around so good
without a cane or dog?

28:25.482 --> 28:27.067
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to pry.

28:29.153 --> 28:31.238
My ears got to be my eyes, man.
Its ...

28:32.031 --> 28:33.282
Everything sounds different.

28:33.365 --> 28:35.451
You know that's why
I wear hard-soled shoes,

28:35.492 --> 28:37.494
so I can hear my footsteps
echo off the wall.

28:37.578 --> 28:40.789
So when I pass by an open
doorway, the sound changes.

28:40.915 --> 28:42.333
Wow. That's cool.

28:42.791 --> 28:46.378
You know you got to learn pretty quick
if you want to get around on your own.

28:46.462 --> 28:47.588
Yeah.

28:48.214 --> 28:50.466
You know, during the war,
there was a whole lot ...

28:50.549 --> 28:52.760
I had to learn fast,
or I wouldn't be here.

28:55.346 --> 28:57.723
Seein' that much death
ain't natural.

28:59.600 --> 29:01.936
Yeah, seein' death ain't natural.

29:06.398 --> 29:08.400
Boys, get from 'round that still.

29:08.484 --> 29:09.860
Y'all know better than that.

29:09.944 --> 29:11.362
Come on, catch me.

29:16.700 --> 29:18.911
Stay from 'round this fire
and get clean.

29:18.994 --> 29:20.579
Dinner will be ready soon.

29:20.663 --> 29:22.122
Hear me, Ray?

29:23.916 --> 29:25.167
I got you. I got you.

29:25.251 --> 29:26.627
No, you didn't. You missed me.

29:26.710 --> 29:28.003
Stop cheatin', Ray.

29:28.045 --> 29:30.673
Okay, you got me.

29:30.756 --> 29:32.508
But I got you back.

29:32.550 --> 29:34.301
I'm not playin' no more.

29:34.552 --> 29:35.719
Sissy!

29:37.429 --> 29:39.807
Come on, Ray.
Let's go swimmin'.

29:41.976 --> 29:44.478
Let's go swim in Mama's washtub.

29:45.521 --> 29:47.648
Ray, come on, Ray, play with me.

29:47.898 --> 29:50.025
You better get down
before Mama sees you.

29:50.067 --> 29:51.569
I'm a giant!

29:55.698 --> 29:57.157
Some giant.

29:58.242 --> 30:01.036
Come on, George.
I ain't playin' this game.

30:02.079 --> 30:03.581
That ain't funny.

30:05.541 --> 30:08.210
Boys, I got some field peas
and rice cooking.

30:08.252 --> 30:10.880
And there's that smothered
corn left from yesterday.

30:10.921 --> 30:14.925
And if you're real good, I might
have two pieces of peach cobbler.

30:15.676 --> 30:18.387
Ray, didn't I tell you
to get in this house?

30:21.765 --> 30:23.392
Dear God, no!

30:28.105 --> 30:29.315
That's Aretha's boy!

30:29.440 --> 30:30.774
Breathe, baby, breathe.

30:30.858 --> 30:34.236
Just breathe, baby, breathe.
Let it out!

30:34.320 --> 30:36.113
Let it out, please!

30:36.280 --> 30:37.615
Breathe for your mama, now.

30:37.698 --> 30:39.033
Come on, George.

30:39.283 --> 30:41.410
Why didn't you do somethin'?

30:41.911 --> 30:43.329
Why didn't you call me?

30:44.914 --> 30:46.582
Help us, Lord!

30:46.624 --> 30:48.250
The Lord done took him home.

30:57.885 --> 30:59.094
All right.

30:59.720 --> 31:01.931
Food and piss stop. Open it up.

31:05.267 --> 31:07.937
The food is hot.
You've got 45 minutes.

31:08.395 --> 31:10.397
- I could eat a horse.
- Where's it?

31:10.564 --> 31:12.566
Follow your nose. Right over there.

31:13.317 --> 31:14.443
Wilbur.

31:14.485 --> 31:15.569
What?

31:15.653 --> 31:17.947
45 minutes ain't enough time.

31:17.988 --> 31:19.490
We need more than that, Jack.

31:19.573 --> 31:21.158
Not to eat, you don't.

31:21.242 --> 31:23.327
Now if you got other business,
you better choose,

31:23.410 --> 31:24.912
because this bus
is rollin' on time.

31:24.995 --> 31:28.249
Come on, Mercedes got
a washroom in the back.

31:28.582 --> 31:31.126
And you, you can smell it.

31:32.836 --> 31:33.837
Jeff.

31:33.921 --> 31:34.922
Yes, sir?

31:35.005 --> 31:36.257
Uh, could you help me in there?

31:36.340 --> 31:37.716
Sure thing, Ray.

31:37.800 --> 31:38.801
Hey, Mercedes.

31:38.884 --> 31:41.679
Hey, baby. I hope you wiped
your feet before you came in here.

31:41.762 --> 31:43.180
- There you go. Come on.
- Take that.

31:43.264 --> 31:45.140
The bathroom's right there
in front of you.

31:45.182 --> 31:46.183
Okay.

31:46.225 --> 31:47.476
You want me to fix you a plate?

31:47.560 --> 31:48.852
Uh, no, I'm ... I'm fine.

31:49.186 --> 31:50.312
All right.

31:50.396 --> 31:52.273
Sweet potato pie it is.

31:53.691 --> 31:54.817
Whoo, let's go, man.

31:54.900 --> 31:56.652
That was a long bus ride,
wasn't it?

31:56.735 --> 31:57.820
Oh, come on, man.

31:57.903 --> 32:00.990
Hey, man!
The can's down the hall.

32:01.073 --> 32:02.950
I know where the can is.
What y'all doing?

32:03.033 --> 32:04.660
Do yourself a favor and leave.

32:04.702 --> 32:06.579
I'll leave when
I'm gettin' ready to leave.

32:06.662 --> 32:08.163
Come on, Fathead, I want in.

32:08.247 --> 32:09.957
This ain't no weed, Ray.

32:10.082 --> 32:12.042
And we ain't snorting no bitch.

32:12.084 --> 32:13.335
This is boy.

32:13.377 --> 32:15.880
Boy'll make your ass
null and void.

32:15.921 --> 32:17.506
So get on out of here, man.

32:17.590 --> 32:19.425
Null and void, just like my life.

32:19.508 --> 32:21.135
I'll be right at home.

32:21.218 --> 32:22.887
Look, I ain't gonna
wait all night.

32:23.012 --> 32:24.680
Hell, it's his funeral, man.

32:26.724 --> 32:28.767
Ray, let's go get
something to eat.

32:28.851 --> 32:30.436
I'll leave when I get a taste.

32:30.519 --> 32:31.687
Ray, what you gonna do, man?

32:31.770 --> 32:33.189
This train's pullin' out, brother.

32:33.272 --> 32:35.107
I ain't having nothin'
to do with this.

32:35.191 --> 32:36.859
- I warned you, Ray.
- Come on, man.

32:36.942 --> 32:38.152
I been warned.

32:38.235 --> 32:39.486
Sit down, Ray. Right there.

32:39.570 --> 32:41.071
I'm gonna take you
on a little ride.

32:41.155 --> 32:43.824
It'll cost you, though.
You got some cash?

32:43.908 --> 32:45.326
Will this do?

32:46.076 --> 32:47.077
That'll do.

32:49.330 --> 32:51.207
Where you been?
Where them other fools?

32:51.248 --> 32:52.750
Come on, get it while it's hot!

32:54.084 --> 32:56.420
You're going to feel
a little pinch.

32:59.089 --> 33:00.716
I ain't givin' up on you, boy.

33:02.134 --> 33:03.677
Feel it, baby?

33:04.845 --> 33:06.639
Just take the ride.

33:07.765 --> 33:09.600
It's better than sex.

33:09.975 --> 33:12.311
There ain't nothin'
better than sex.

33:17.775 --> 33:19.860
♪ We will walk ♪

33:19.944 --> 33:24.865
♪ through the streets of the city ♪

33:25.449 --> 33:27.076
♪ Of the city ♪

33:27.952 --> 33:31.372
♪ Where our loved ones ♪

33:31.455 --> 33:36.418
♪ have gone on before ♪

33:39.088 --> 33:43.759
♪ We will stand on the banks ♪

33:44.426 --> 33:47.721
♪ of the river ♪

33:47.805 --> 33:49.723
♪ Of the river ♪

33:50.099 --> 33:53.060
♪ Where we'll meet ♪

33:53.269 --> 33:58.190
♪ to part no more ♪

34:01.485 --> 34:03.654
♪ I pray ♪

34:03.737 --> 34:04.780
♪ I pray ♪

34:04.864 --> 34:07.533
♪ Be free from now on ♪

34:07.658 --> 34:10.119
♪ Pray to you, Lord ♪

34:10.202 --> 34:15.123
♪ Where our true ones have gone ♪

34:15.833 --> 34:18.502
♪ Gone before ♪

34:18.585 --> 34:20.504
♪ Gone before ♪

34:21.213 --> 34:25.801
♪ We will stand on the banks ♪

34:26.552 --> 34:29.889
♪ of the river ♪

34:31.974 --> 34:34.643
♪ Where we'll meet ♪

34:34.685 --> 34:39.315
♪ to part no more ♪

35:09.553 --> 35:12.598
Ray, come on, let me put this
salve on I got from Dr. McLeod.

35:12.681 --> 35:14.183
No, I don't like it. It stings.

35:14.266 --> 35:15.726
Boy, get up here.

35:16.310 --> 35:19.230
I paid a whole dollar for it.
It better work.

35:19.313 --> 35:21.774
Now hold up your head,
like the doctor says.

35:21.857 --> 35:23.817
This is gonna make you feel better.

35:28.239 --> 35:30.407
Ray, come on in for dinner.

35:30.491 --> 35:32.785
And stop rubbin' those eyes.

35:44.755 --> 35:46.757
Ray, I won't beat around
the bush with you.

35:46.840 --> 35:48.092
You're goin' blind.

35:48.175 --> 35:51.554
The doctor's sayin' there's nothing they
can do, so we got to do it ourselves.

35:51.595 --> 35:52.680
Yes, ma'am, I know, but ...

35:52.763 --> 35:53.722
Stop it.

35:53.764 --> 35:55.349
Stop it right now.

35:55.432 --> 35:57.351
We ain't got no time
for no tears.

35:57.434 --> 35:59.061
Ain't nobody gonna
have no pity on you ...

35:59.144 --> 36:00.437
just 'cause you're goin' blind.

36:00.521 --> 36:01.689
Now wipe them eyes.

36:01.772 --> 36:03.148
Yes, ma'am.

36:05.150 --> 36:07.444
Okay, I'll show you
how to do something once.

36:07.528 --> 36:09.154
I'll help you if you mess up twice.

36:09.238 --> 36:10.906
But the third time,
you're on your own,

36:10.990 --> 36:13.367
'cause that's the way
it is in the world.

36:13.450 --> 36:14.910
All right, now get up.

36:16.787 --> 36:19.999
Remember, you goin' blind,
but you ain't stupid.

36:22.126 --> 36:23.669
Remember how many stairs
there were?

36:23.752 --> 36:25.087
Four.

36:25.129 --> 36:28.632
Good. You're gonna have to learn
how to use your memory.

36:28.716 --> 36:29.884
Now turn around.

36:29.967 --> 36:31.886
I want you
to hold out your hands,

36:31.969 --> 36:34.889
and use them as your eyes,
and find the door.

36:36.098 --> 36:39.101
Good. That's real good, baby.

36:49.445 --> 36:50.404
Hi.

36:57.286 --> 37:00.998
♪ Baby, let me hold your hand ♪

37:05.252 --> 37:09.006
♪ Till I make you understand ♪

37:10.883 --> 37:13.135
♪ Oh, baby ♪

37:16.722 --> 37:19.767
♪ Let me hold your hand ♪

37:27.399 --> 37:30.027
♪ I really true believe ♪

37:30.110 --> 37:33.781
This fool makes one record, and you'd
think he's the star of the band.

37:33.864 --> 37:36.659
Well, he's got somethin',
ain't he?

37:37.284 --> 37:39.161
His wax won't even hit the charts.

37:39.828 --> 37:41.664
You're still the man.

37:43.290 --> 37:45.668
♪ I want you to know ♪

37:47.920 --> 37:49.213
♪ I'm in love ♪

37:49.296 --> 37:50.297
She wasn't that fine.

37:50.381 --> 37:51.757
There's somethin' wrong with you.

37:51.840 --> 37:55.176
No, man, she's fine. She's fine.
You leave her alone.

37:55.887 --> 37:57.888
Look at Ray.

37:57.888 --> 37:58.764
You see that?

37:58.847 --> 38:00.516
He feels her wrist
'cause he figures ...

38:00.558 --> 38:02.852
that's the way to tell
if she's good-looking or not.

38:02.935 --> 38:05.354
You know I had my eye on you
all night long.

38:05.437 --> 38:07.439
Oh, he right this time.

38:09.400 --> 38:12.403
See what a little fame does
to Null and Void?

38:12.736 --> 38:15.906
Anybody see that fine-looking
gal in the yellow dress?

38:17.491 --> 38:18.617
You hear this man?

38:18.701 --> 38:20.160
You snooze, you lose.

38:20.244 --> 38:21.996
We gonna dock your pay, man.

38:22.079 --> 38:23.998
That's $2 off of your busride.

38:28.794 --> 38:32.298
♪ Baby, I want you by my side ♪

38:35.217 --> 38:36.468
♪ I do ♪

38:40.180 --> 38:42.766
♪ I want you to know ♪

38:45.060 --> 38:48.522
♪ Our love we will never hide ♪

38:49.857 --> 38:52.151
♪ Oh, no, no, no ♪

38:53.944 --> 38:55.613
All right, who's next?

38:56.614 --> 38:58.032
It's a shame, Jimmy.

38:58.115 --> 39:00.075
You're just gonna
piss this right up your arm.

39:00.159 --> 39:02.703
You don't tell me
what to do with my money.

39:03.120 --> 39:06.749
All right, come on. Step up.
The $1 sensation.

39:11.962 --> 39:13.756
You wanna keep counting?

39:13.839 --> 39:15.591
What's the matter with you, boy?

39:15.633 --> 39:17.051
$50 ain't good enough for you?

39:17.134 --> 39:19.220
That ain't $50. Keep counting.

39:19.803 --> 39:23.098
I guess you want charity, since
that record of yours ain't selling.

39:26.185 --> 39:27.645
Get him off my back!

39:32.483 --> 39:34.109
Break it up!

39:34.276 --> 39:35.945
What the hell's going on in here?

39:36.487 --> 39:39.323
The blind sensation don't like
the money I'm trying to pay him!

39:39.406 --> 39:40.449
He's cheating me! I quit!

39:40.533 --> 39:42.201
Oh, you lying son of a bitch!

39:42.493 --> 39:44.620
Don't be fighting nobody
that can see!

39:44.662 --> 39:47.414
Listen, I ain't runnnin' around
lookin' for singles for this chump!

39:47.498 --> 39:48.582
There's $50 here, Ray.

39:48.666 --> 39:49.625
You see that, fool?

39:49.708 --> 39:52.545
Shut up, Wilbur! Ray, from now on,
I'll handle your pay myself.

39:52.628 --> 39:53.587
I'm tired of this!

39:53.671 --> 39:55.422
I'll tell Jack to
find you somebody else!

39:55.506 --> 39:56.715
You sure? It's cold out there.

39:56.799 --> 39:58.801
Don't worry about me,
I can take care of myself.

39:58.884 --> 40:01.053
- Ray!
- Damn it, Wilbur!

40:01.136 --> 40:02.137
Let him go!

40:02.221 --> 40:03.722
What we gonna do now?

40:11.522 --> 40:15.234
"After the death of Moses, the
Lord spake unto Joshua saying:

40:15.317 --> 40:17.695
Moses my servant is dead.

40:17.778 --> 40:20.239
Now therefore arise.
Go over to Jordan.

40:20.322 --> 40:21.448
Be not afraid,

40:21.532 --> 40:23.617
For the Lord thy God is with thee."

40:23.701 --> 40:25.160
Mr. Charles.

40:25.661 --> 40:26.996
Who is it?

40:27.121 --> 40:28.789
Mr. Charles,
my name is Ahmet Ertegun.

40:28.873 --> 40:30.457
May I have a moment of your time?

40:34.211 --> 40:36.088
What do you want, man?
I'm at church.

40:36.171 --> 40:38.465
I'm sorry. I'll come back later.

40:38.591 --> 40:40.634
You're here now. What do you want?

40:41.927 --> 40:44.054
My company, Atlantic Records,
has acquired ...

40:44.138 --> 40:46.307
your contract from Swing Time.

40:46.807 --> 40:48.517
I'd like to discuss your future.

40:48.601 --> 40:51.437
Hold on. Don't jive me now.
I ain't for sale.

40:51.687 --> 40:53.147
May I sit down?

40:55.816 --> 40:57.776
You see, Mr. Charles,

40:58.485 --> 41:00.613
Jack Lauderdale has found himself,

41:00.738 --> 41:02.865
shall we say, a little overextended,

41:03.324 --> 41:06.118
and has had to
unload some of his talent.

41:06.202 --> 41:08.162
When your name
came up, I jumped at ...

41:08.245 --> 41:10.164
the chance to work with you.
I'm a big fan.

41:10.247 --> 41:12.124
What if I want to go
to another company?

41:12.208 --> 41:14.627
There's a guy out there right now
that is willing to pay me ...

41:14.710 --> 41:17.046
seven cents a record.
Can you do that?

41:17.421 --> 41:20.216
Man, I could promise you
15 cents a record,

41:21.091 --> 41:24.511
but you won't get it any more
than he'll pay you seven.

41:26.263 --> 41:29.391
What I will do is promise you
five cents a record ...

41:29.600 --> 41:31.894
and pay you five cents
a record.

41:32.645 --> 41:35.898
If you think pennies,
Mr. Charles, you get pennies.

41:36.774 --> 41:38.526
You think dollars,

41:39.527 --> 41:41.111
you get dollars.

41:43.113 --> 41:45.866
I like how you put
things together, man.

41:46.367 --> 41:47.868
Ahem, you know what?

41:48.369 --> 41:50.871
Omelet, you're all right with me.

41:51.288 --> 41:52.498
- Ahmet.
- Ahmet.

41:52.581 --> 41:53.749
What kind of name is that?

41:53.791 --> 41:55.042
I'm Turkish.

41:55.125 --> 41:56.335
Well, you know what?

41:56.418 --> 41:59.296
I guess Jack Lauderdale's bad
luck is my good fortune.

41:59.463 --> 42:02.508
I knew that Atlantic Records
was bigger than Swing Time.

42:02.591 --> 42:05.135
You guys do good music.
I dig Atlantic.

42:05.219 --> 42:06.679
You could have fooled me.

42:06.762 --> 42:09.431
Well, you know, I gotta keep
my eye on you city boys.

42:10.015 --> 42:11.851
Down home,
we call it "country dumb."

42:13.978 --> 42:15.813
Hey, man, it ain't Turkish.

42:20.860 --> 42:23.153
♪ Went to see my sweetheart ♪

42:24.071 --> 42:26.824
♪ Last night around about ten ♪

42:27.408 --> 42:30.786
♪ She said, move, sweet papa ♪

42:31.620 --> 42:34.123
♪ Squeeze me every now and then ♪

42:34.373 --> 42:36.125
What do you think?

42:36.166 --> 42:38.586
Man, nobody wants
another Nat King Cole.

42:39.753 --> 42:41.714
♪ 'Cause she sleep that way ♪

42:41.797 --> 42:44.800
♪ The midnight hour ♪

42:46.051 --> 42:48.637
♪ Has found me lonely ♪

42:49.889 --> 42:51.807
♪ So unhappy ♪

42:53.100 --> 42:54.852
♪ As I can be ♪

42:55.019 --> 42:57.897
Ahmet, it's just
like Charles Brown.

43:00.107 --> 43:02.526
Okay, I'll talk to him.

43:05.154 --> 43:07.990
All right, fellas, that's a cut.
That's a cut, fellas.

43:08.657 --> 43:09.909
Fellas!

43:09.992 --> 43:11.327
Band can take five.

43:11.452 --> 43:12.786
He just don't get it.

43:12.870 --> 43:15.831
You either sound original,
or you got nothin'.

43:15.956 --> 43:18.167
Ahmet, what'd you think of that?

43:18.292 --> 43:21.462
Ray, I want to tell you something,
and I don't want you to take it wrong.

43:21.545 --> 43:22.838
Then give it to me right.

43:22.922 --> 43:26.342
I signed you because I sensed
something special in you ...

43:26.383 --> 43:29.595
not because you sound like
Nat Cole or Charles Brown.

43:29.678 --> 43:31.513
I thought you like what I do.

43:31.555 --> 43:33.516
We ... we love the timbre
of your voice,

43:33.557 --> 43:35.809
we like your virtuosity,
your energy ...

43:35.893 --> 43:37.144
But not my music.

43:37.228 --> 43:38.646
Come on, man, I didn't say that.

43:39.146 --> 43:41.148
Ahmet, this is what I do, man.

43:41.232 --> 43:43.359
I gotta make a living.
This is what the people want.

43:43.442 --> 43:45.027
I don't know no other way.

43:45.110 --> 43:46.862
We got to help you find one.

43:46.904 --> 43:49.240
Look, let's try a little
change of pace, okay?

43:49.323 --> 43:50.699
You're familiar with stride piano?

43:50.783 --> 43:54.078
You kidding me, man? The man who I
learned the piano from is a stride player.

43:54.161 --> 43:57.164
Okay, I got a song.
It's called "The Mess Around".

43:57.248 --> 43:59.083
"The Mess Around."
Cute title. Who wrote it?

43:59.166 --> 44:00.543
I did.

44:00.793 --> 44:02.211
Ah, you wrote it.

44:02.294 --> 44:03.295
Yeah.

44:03.712 --> 44:05.047
Well, sing it to me, man.

44:05.339 --> 44:06.507
- Sing it?
- Yeah.

44:06.590 --> 44:08.217
It ain't like
I can read the lyrics.

44:08.300 --> 44:10.886
Okay.
Well, it's the key of G.

44:10.970 --> 44:12.388
Okay. Key of G.

44:13.556 --> 44:14.515
Uh-huh.

44:15.349 --> 44:16.350
Yeah.

44:16.517 --> 44:19.353
Yeah, but it's a kind of
Pete Johnson thing.

44:19.436 --> 44:20.813
Pete Johnson.

44:22.606 --> 44:24.275
Yeah, yeah, that's it.

44:24.400 --> 44:26.443
You like that?
Here we go. Two, three, four.

44:26.527 --> 44:29.822
♪ You can talk
about the pit barbecue ♪

44:29.905 --> 44:32.116
♪ The band was jumpin',
the people, too ♪

44:32.199 --> 44:34.201
♪ They're doin' the mess around ♪

44:35.035 --> 44:37.037
♪ They're doin' the mess around ♪

44:37.955 --> 44:39.874
♪ They're doin' the mess around ♪

44:39.957 --> 44:41.917
♪ Everybody doin'
the mess around ♪

44:42.001 --> 44:44.169
All right, that's good.
Let me take it from here.

44:44.253 --> 44:47.798
♪ Now this band's gonna
play from nine to one ♪

44:47.882 --> 44:50.467
♪ Everybody here's gonna
have some fun ♪

44:50.593 --> 44:52.344
♪ Doin' the mess around ♪

44:53.137 --> 44:55.347
♪ Ah, doin' the mess around ♪

44:56.974 --> 44:59.143
♪ They doin' the mess around ♪

44:59.268 --> 45:01.353
♪ Everybody doin'
the mess around ♪

45:03.480 --> 45:06.942
♪ Now you see that girl
with that diamond ring ♪

45:07.568 --> 45:10.362
♪ She knows
how to shake that thing ♪

45:10.821 --> 45:12.364
♪ Mess around ♪

45:12.948 --> 45:14.909
♪ I declare she can mess around ♪

45:16.493 --> 45:18.245
♪ Ah, mess around ♪

45:18.662 --> 45:20.998
♪ Everybody do the mess around ♪

45:27.087 --> 45:28.589
Now we got something!

45:28.672 --> 45:30.174
That's all right there.

45:31.675 --> 45:32.968
What do you think, Ahmet?

45:33.010 --> 45:34.053
Great, Ray!

45:34.136 --> 45:35.262
Unbelievable!

45:35.346 --> 45:36.430
Who's that?

45:37.431 --> 45:39.642
Ray, I want you to meet
my new partner, Jerry.

45:39.725 --> 45:41.268
Mr. Ray Charles, Jerry Wexler.

45:41.352 --> 45:42.353
Hey.

45:42.436 --> 45:45.481
Don't worry, Ray. I'm going to
step back, I'm gonna watch,

45:45.564 --> 45:47.983
I'm gonna learn how to produce
a record. I'm in awe.

45:48.025 --> 45:49.276
That was out of sight.

45:49.360 --> 45:51.153
That's some running
and riffing, man!

45:51.445 --> 45:53.155
Well, this'll make you shout, man.

46:01.247 --> 46:03.999
We're listening to that
new recording, Mess Around ...

46:04.083 --> 46:06.377
by Atlantic recording artist,
Ray Charles.

46:06.460 --> 46:09.964
And we have the gentleman
live here in the KCOH studios.

46:10.047 --> 46:13.092
So, Ray, when you're not making your
own music, what do you listen to?

46:13.175 --> 46:16.845
You know what, the fact is, King Bee,
I really and truly love gospel.

46:16.887 --> 46:19.807
One of my favorite groups
is from right here in Houston:

46:19.890 --> 46:21.725
The Cecil Shaw Singers.

46:21.934 --> 46:25.479
You heard it: Ray Charles endorses
Houston's own Cecil Shaw.

46:25.563 --> 46:27.481
We'll be playing
gospel all day Sunday ...

46:27.565 --> 46:29.233
but right now,
let's hear some more ...

46:29.316 --> 46:30.943
of that Mess Around
by Ray Charles.

46:31.026 --> 46:32.361
K.B., line 1.

46:34.738 --> 46:36.073
King Bee.

46:37.783 --> 46:38.784
Mmm-hmm.

46:39.785 --> 46:41.453
Yeah, he's right here.

46:42.079 --> 46:44.665
Miss Della Antwine
of the Cecil Shaw Singers.

46:48.127 --> 46:49.962
Hello, Miss Antwine.

46:50.379 --> 46:53.132
You sung tenor in
Jesus Is My Shepherd, right?

46:53.215 --> 46:54.425
Yes.

46:55.259 --> 46:57.011
How did you pick me out?

46:57.094 --> 47:00.055
Actually,
I ... I hear like you see.

47:00.806 --> 47:03.851
Like that hummingbird outside
the window, for instance.

47:10.065 --> 47:11.317
I can't hear her.

47:11.400 --> 47:12.651
You have to listen.

47:30.711 --> 47:31.754
Yes.

47:31.837 --> 47:32.838
Yeah.

47:33.130 --> 47:34.256
Yes, you can.

47:34.340 --> 47:35.382
OH-OH.

47:35.466 --> 47:36.425
You hear that?

47:36.508 --> 47:37.551
What?

47:38.302 --> 47:40.429
Her heart just skipped a beat.

47:42.681 --> 47:44.558
Oh, did you like my record?

47:44.850 --> 47:47.228
The one that King Bee was playin'?

47:48.646 --> 47:50.272
It was very nice.

47:50.523 --> 47:52.733
Different than the others.

47:53.317 --> 47:55.236
I've heard a lot of your music.

47:55.319 --> 47:56.862
Was it very nice, too?

47:56.946 --> 47:59.198
Look, Miss Antwine, if you
don't really like the record,

47:59.281 --> 48:02.660
you ain't got to beat around the bush
with me. I mean, my mama never did.

48:02.743 --> 48:05.037
It's not that I don't
enjoy your music.

48:05.120 --> 48:07.456
It's just that I feel
I've heard it before.

48:07.498 --> 48:10.042
I keep wondering what the
real Ray Charles sound like.

48:10.125 --> 48:11.585
Ray Charles? Who's he?

48:11.669 --> 48:13.587
Nobody, if you don't know.

48:13.671 --> 48:14.630
Huh?

48:15.464 --> 48:17.925
Sorry. I should have
kept my mouth shut.

48:18.008 --> 48:20.177
Oh, no, no.
Then you wouldn't be you.

48:21.387 --> 48:23.806
You know, it's not like
I haven't heard that before.

48:23.848 --> 48:27.184
I guess I just, uh, never
really listened, that's all.

48:29.395 --> 48:32.356
Ain't nobody ever put
it that sweet, I guess.

48:49.582 --> 48:51.500
You know what,
Miss Della Bea Antwine?

48:51.542 --> 48:53.669
You really are a country girl.
You know that?

48:53.752 --> 48:55.713
Yes.
How'd you know?

48:55.796 --> 48:57.840
I could tell by
the way you ordered.

48:57.923 --> 49:00.092
"Let me get molasses
with my cornbread."

49:01.343 --> 49:03.012
Were you raised on a farm?

49:03.095 --> 49:05.931
My mother did a little
sharecropping in Florida.

49:06.015 --> 49:07.474
Is she still there?

49:07.558 --> 49:10.394
God bless her heart, she passed
away when I went to school.

49:10.477 --> 49:11.979
Ray, I'm sorry.

49:12.438 --> 49:14.148
She never was real healthy.

49:14.231 --> 49:16.775
She just worked herself
to death, poor thing.

49:16.901 --> 49:19.653
That's why she didn't want me
carrying around no tin cup.

49:19.737 --> 49:21.447
The kids I went to school with,

49:21.530 --> 49:24.200
they were doing basket-weavin'
and wickerwork.

49:25.075 --> 49:27.369
But not you. Because of your gift.

49:27.494 --> 49:29.121
Because of my ears.

49:29.413 --> 49:31.332
See, I can mimic
damn near anybody,

49:31.415 --> 49:34.084
and I ... I ... I ... I make
a pretty decent living at it.

49:34.168 --> 49:36.212
It's just, if I
change my style up ...

49:36.295 --> 49:37.838
and people really don't dig it,

49:37.922 --> 49:40.174
I mean, what am I
left with, you know?

49:40.424 --> 49:42.760
I mean, when you're blind,
Miss Antwine,

49:42.927 --> 49:45.012
you ain't got that many choices.

49:46.263 --> 49:48.724
Seem to me like you got all
the choices in the world.

49:49.934 --> 49:51.727
God gave you the gift to sound ...

49:51.769 --> 49:54.063
like anybody you please,
even yourself.

49:55.814 --> 49:58.025
We're here. This is where I live.

49:59.151 --> 50:00.986
Well, you think
the preacher'd let me in?

50:01.070 --> 50:03.405
I mean, uh, I'm a sinner,
but I need a little prayer.

50:03.447 --> 50:05.950
His wife don't like
me having male company.

50:06.075 --> 50:09.203
Well, tell him there's
a soul out here that needs savin'.

50:09.954 --> 50:13.374
You know what, Miss Antwine,
you really got me thinkin'.

50:15.209 --> 50:16.669
About what?

50:16.794 --> 50:20.089
About my life. About my music.

50:22.216 --> 50:23.717
About everything.

50:25.970 --> 50:29.431
Ray, don't ... don't you think
we're movin' a little fast?

50:31.392 --> 50:33.143
Listen, I'm ... I'm gonna
go to New York ...

50:33.227 --> 50:35.729
for a couple of weeks,
and when I get back,

50:36.146 --> 50:38.607
you can take it as
slow as you want.

50:41.277 --> 50:43.112
All right, Mr. Charles.

50:44.488 --> 50:46.240
All right, Miss Antwine.

50:46.657 --> 50:48.284
I'll see you in a couple of weeks.

50:48.325 --> 50:50.369
Well, hold on, now.
Let me call you a cab.

50:50.452 --> 50:52.121
I got it. Three blocks up,

50:52.204 --> 50:54.915
left for two, right for one.

50:54.999 --> 50:56.709
Fifteen giant steps,

50:56.792 --> 50:58.711
and I'm at the
Crystal White Hotel. Hello.

51:05.968 --> 51:08.554
"Mess Around" was
a positive step for us, Ray.

51:08.637 --> 51:09.763
We're making progress.

51:09.847 --> 51:11.974
Oh, come on, Ahmet.
Now, you've been nice to me.

51:12.057 --> 51:13.809
But I haven't given
you guys any hits.

51:13.893 --> 51:15.436
Atlantic Records
has been good to me,

51:15.519 --> 51:17.229
but if you want me to do
something special,

51:17.313 --> 51:18.647
I'm gonna need my own band.

51:19.148 --> 51:22.359
Oh, man. Taking a band out on
the road costs a mint, Ray.

51:22.443 --> 51:25.487
I mean, even Joe Morris is struggling.
His band's had a hit record.

51:25.571 --> 51:27.406
But, Ahmet, listen,
I'm not Joe Morris.

51:27.489 --> 51:29.742
Man, you told me if I think
pennies, I get pennies.

51:29.825 --> 51:31.702
I'm thinking dollars, man.

51:33.037 --> 51:35.873
Ruth Brown's got
a tour booked in Georgia.

51:36.999 --> 51:38.209
She needs a band.

51:38.292 --> 51:39.293
I ... I'll take it.

51:39.376 --> 51:42.129
I could write the charts
for her, I ... I could do backup,

51:42.213 --> 51:44.256
and also be an openin' act.

51:47.218 --> 51:48.552
Okay.

51:48.677 --> 51:50.930
But you're going to be
financially responsible.

51:51.013 --> 51:52.932
You're gonna have
to make it work, Ray.

51:53.015 --> 51:55.518
Yeah, yeah, I'm gonna make it
do what it do, baby.

51:55.601 --> 51:56.977
Yeah.

52:09.114 --> 52:10.115
Ray!

52:10.366 --> 52:12.785
Miss Antwine, it's been two weeks.

52:12.868 --> 52:14.578
It's been three.

52:20.251 --> 52:22.711
Now, where's the preacher at?
And the wife?

52:22.836 --> 52:24.922
They in Dallas till Monday.

52:25.005 --> 52:26.757
Well, hallelujah!

52:36.976 --> 52:38.394
Della Bea.

52:39.270 --> 52:41.063
Kind of like a honey bee, right?

52:44.984 --> 52:46.652
Can I call you Bea?

52:47.653 --> 52:49.947
Yeah, I'd like that.

52:52.825 --> 52:56.662
There's only been two cats that
I ever really trusted in my life.

52:58.289 --> 53:01.417
There's Jeff Brown, he's going
to be my tour manager,

53:02.293 --> 53:04.587
Fathead Newman, my tenor man ...

53:06.797 --> 53:08.257
and now you.

53:15.973 --> 53:17.349
But you gotta do me a favor.

53:17.433 --> 53:19.518
Bea, you gotta
always tell me the truth.

53:19.602 --> 53:21.729
Oh, yeah.
Just like you did before.

53:22.605 --> 53:25.566
Don't feel sorry for me
just 'cause I'm blind.

53:26.692 --> 53:29.195
How could I pity
someone I admire?

53:34.200 --> 53:35.701
Can I play something for you?

53:35.784 --> 53:37.369
- Now?
- Yeah.

53:37.453 --> 53:38.579
No, Ray.

53:38.662 --> 53:40.581
Yeah, right now.
Right now. I'm gonna ...

53:40.664 --> 53:41.790
Ray!

53:45.669 --> 53:47.546
It's right there.
You got it.

53:47.671 --> 53:48.839
Okay.

53:48.923 --> 53:50.132
Yeah, yeah, this will work.

53:51.342 --> 53:53.636
Now you go ahead and play.
I'm gonna close these drapes.

53:53.719 --> 53:54.720
All right.

53:54.803 --> 53:56.305
I don't want no
neighbors looking in.

53:56.388 --> 53:57.806
♪ Well ♪

53:58.349 --> 53:59.975
♪ I got a woman ♪

54:00.976 --> 54:02.394
♪ way over town ♪

54:02.978 --> 54:04.480
♪ She's good to me ♪

54:05.523 --> 54:06.774
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

54:07.608 --> 54:09.109
♪ I got a woman ♪

54:09.985 --> 54:11.445
♪ Way over town ♪

54:11.529 --> 54:12.488
Ray.

54:12.571 --> 54:13.822
♪ She's good to me ♪

54:14.782 --> 54:16.158
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

54:16.242 --> 54:17.243
Ray!

54:17.326 --> 54:18.577
♪ She give me money ♪

54:18.661 --> 54:20.120
Ray. Ray, that's sacrilegious.

54:20.204 --> 54:21.247
♪ When I'm in need ♪

54:21.330 --> 54:22.498
What ... what?

54:22.581 --> 54:24.291
It's a gospel song.

54:25.042 --> 54:27.086
I know what it is.
I wrote it.

54:27.711 --> 54:30.172
I mean, you told me
to find my own voice.

54:30.256 --> 54:31.840
Well, Bea, this is it.

54:31.924 --> 54:36.053
But it ... it ain't ... It ain't right
to be changing gospel music into this.

54:36.136 --> 54:38.013
Into what? Is it ...
Is it devil music?

54:38.097 --> 54:41.141
Evil music? Do you think ...
Do you think I'm evil, Bea?

54:41.725 --> 54:43.978
Look, I've been
performing gospel ...

54:44.061 --> 54:46.230
and blues all my life.
It's who I am.

54:46.814 --> 54:50.317
And if I'm gonna do my own thing,
I ... I gotta be natural, right?

54:51.902 --> 54:54.488
I'm singing about
my feelings for you.

54:54.947 --> 54:56.615
About how I love you.

54:59.159 --> 55:01.412
What could be more
natural than that?

55:02.663 --> 55:03.914
Huh, Bea?

55:04.498 --> 55:05.833
Tell me.

55:06.917 --> 55:08.961
More natural than me and you.

55:09.503 --> 55:10.504
Ray.

55:15.050 --> 55:16.886
♪ I got a woman ♪

55:17.595 --> 55:19.555
♪ Way over town ♪

55:21.265 --> 55:22.683
♪ good to me ♪

55:24.101 --> 55:25.311
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

55:26.770 --> 55:29.190
So we bite the bullet,
we cancel the tour dates.

55:29.273 --> 55:31.108
But what the hell
are we gonna tell Ray?

55:31.192 --> 55:33.027
We just have
to tell him the truth:

55:33.110 --> 55:34.904
Ruth Brown's pregnant,
so there's no tour.

55:34.945 --> 55:36.739
What about LaVern Baker?

55:36.864 --> 55:38.866
Get LaVern Baker to take the tour.

55:38.949 --> 55:41.118
She doesn't have a record.
There's nothing to promote.

55:41.202 --> 55:43.370
You and Jesse get up there,
write a couple of songs,

55:43.412 --> 55:44.830
let's get her in the studio.

55:44.914 --> 55:46.582
It's gonna take
a month to do that ...

55:46.665 --> 55:48.626
What are we gonna do?
We got to do somethin'.

55:48.709 --> 55:50.377
Ray's got a whole
new band up there.

55:50.419 --> 55:52.755
How the hell did he put
together a band so fast?

55:52.838 --> 55:55.257
Boss! Boss, they're here.

55:55.341 --> 55:58.135
Come on. Let's get together
so we can show 'em this.

55:58.219 --> 55:59.261
... break this to Ray.

55:59.345 --> 56:01.680
Oh, you're gonna let
me break it to Ray?

56:01.764 --> 56:02.723
Why me?

56:02.806 --> 56:04.141
Because Ruth Brown was your idea.

56:04.225 --> 56:07.686
Ruth Brown is a good idea, Ruth Brown
was a good idea, and still is a good idea.

56:07.770 --> 56:08.729
Shh!

56:08.812 --> 56:10.064
♪ That's good to me ♪

56:10.814 --> 56:12.316
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

56:13.067 --> 56:15.069
♪ I got a woman ♪

56:15.945 --> 56:17.655
♪ Way over town ♪

56:18.322 --> 56:19.823
♪ Good to me ♪

56:20.824 --> 56:22.368
♪ Whoa, yeah ♪

56:22.785 --> 56:24.703
♪ She give me money ♪

56:25.412 --> 56:27.623
♪ When I'm in need ♪

56:27.957 --> 56:29.917
♪ Yeah, she's the kind of ♪

56:30.584 --> 56:32.086
♪ friend indeed ♪

56:32.836 --> 56:34.129
♪ I got a woman ♪

56:34.255 --> 56:35.256
Ahmet.

56:35.464 --> 56:36.549
Yeah.

56:36.632 --> 56:38.467
We gotta get this on wax.

56:39.009 --> 56:40.094
Oh, yeah.

56:40.427 --> 56:41.428
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

56:41.595 --> 56:45.015
Hear that, New York?
The sound is huge!

56:45.099 --> 56:47.810
But there's only seven cats
on this record.

56:47.852 --> 56:50.437
This is the new
Ray Charles, baby,

56:50.479 --> 56:52.606
and there's nothing
out there like it!

56:52.690 --> 56:55.609
And you heard it first
on The Moondog Show!

56:57.236 --> 56:58.904
♪ Just for me ♪

56:59.697 --> 57:01.156
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

57:01.907 --> 57:03.367
♪ She give me money ♪

57:04.451 --> 57:07.121
The Shaw Agency's the best booker
on the Chitlin' Circuit,

57:07.204 --> 57:08.497
that's my opinion.

57:08.539 --> 57:10.583
Milt Shaw, meet Ray Charles.

57:10.666 --> 57:12.501
Ray, It was
Milt's dad, Billy,

57:12.543 --> 57:15.170
who first drew my attention
to a certain blind pianist ...

57:15.212 --> 57:17.214
when he was
booking Lowell Fulson.

57:17.298 --> 57:19.717
Ray Charles.
We believe in your talent.

57:19.800 --> 57:22.386
We wanna be
in the Ray Charles business.

57:22.469 --> 57:24.889
We've already got you
booked on a 10-city tour ...

57:24.972 --> 57:26.473
with Roy Milton's Solid Senders ...

57:26.515 --> 57:27.725
Oh, Roy Milton, I love him.

57:27.808 --> 57:30.686
... and Tangula,
the Exotic Shake Dancer.

57:30.895 --> 57:33.439
She is gorgeous.

57:33.564 --> 57:34.857
Ray, I gotta tell you,

57:34.940 --> 57:37.443
we think you're onto
something very big here.

57:37.526 --> 57:40.613
Nobody's ever combined
R&B and gospel before.

57:40.696 --> 57:42.072
"I've Got A Woman" is a smash.

57:42.156 --> 57:44.992
You better start thinking about a
follow-up, my friend. Right now.

57:45.075 --> 57:47.203
You know, this sounds good.
I gotta run to Texas ...

57:47.286 --> 57:49.872
and take care of some business,
and, I'll be right back.

57:49.955 --> 57:52.541
Well, make it fast.
I'm ready to sell, sell, sell.

57:52.625 --> 57:55.878
A-a-as long as you book
me in front of Tangula.

57:55.961 --> 57:57.713
Della, hold on!
Let me get my camera.

57:57.796 --> 57:59.131
Let me get one picture.

57:59.215 --> 58:01.383
Y'all, y'all,
stay right there! Ray!

58:02.343 --> 58:03.969
Della, let me get one picture!

58:04.053 --> 58:06.055
Come on. One picture, Della!
Come on, now.

58:07.348 --> 58:08.516
Be careful, Ray.

58:08.557 --> 58:10.226
These are your last steps
of freedom, man.

58:10.309 --> 58:11.602
Don't open that door.

58:11.685 --> 58:14.522
Ray, you gotta carry her
over the threshold.

58:22.071 --> 58:24.406
To the right, Ray!
To the right, now!

58:27.576 --> 58:29.328
Ray, you need some help?

58:29.411 --> 58:31.247
You sure you know
what you're doing?

58:31.288 --> 58:33.499
♪ He knows a woman's place ♪

58:33.582 --> 58:35.125
♪ Right there now, in her home ♪

58:35.209 --> 58:36.669
♪ I got a woman ♪

58:42.341 --> 58:43.342
Ray.

58:45.135 --> 58:46.136
Ray.

58:47.555 --> 58:49.223
Can I come in?

58:50.474 --> 58:52.059
H-H-Hold on.

58:52.184 --> 58:53.769
What's goin' on, Ray?

58:58.023 --> 58:59.692
Open this door.

59:00.901 --> 59:02.778
Why are you locking doors
on me, Ray?

59:03.988 --> 59:05.197
You know the place is small.

59:05.281 --> 59:06.657
We gotta have a little privacy.

59:06.740 --> 59:09.159
Uh, what we need is
a little more room.

59:09.243 --> 59:12.496
You know, we're gonna need some
space while we start a family.

59:13.789 --> 59:16.959
Well, Bea, you know I'm gonna be
on the road for most of the year.

59:17.001 --> 59:18.002
Ray.

59:19.336 --> 59:22.381
I'm just thinking, what if
I'm not a good father?

59:22.923 --> 59:24.466
My daddy was never around.

59:24.550 --> 59:26.719
And he had 3 different families.

59:28.679 --> 59:29.930
Well you,

59:31.015 --> 59:34.185
are gonna have one,
starting right now.

59:34.268 --> 59:35.269
Right now?

59:35.352 --> 59:36.312
Mmm-hmm.

59:37.188 --> 59:38.606
Well, what do you think?

59:39.815 --> 59:40.774
That's all is what I know.

59:42.234 --> 59:43.611
♪ I know ♪

59:43.819 --> 59:45.946
♪ Hallelujah, I just love her so ♪

01:00:05.382 --> 01:00:07.801
♪ Now, if I call her
on the telephone ♪

01:00:08.552 --> 01:00:10.596
♪ And tell her that I'm all alone ♪

01:00:11.514 --> 01:00:13.766
♪ By the time I count
from one to four ♪

01:00:14.433 --> 01:00:15.476
♪ I hear her ♪

01:00:15.851 --> 01:00:16.810
♪ on my door ♪

01:00:17.770 --> 01:00:19.772
Stop it!
Y'all done lost your minds!

01:00:19.855 --> 01:00:20.898
Stop all this stuff!

01:00:20.981 --> 01:00:22.024
You need to be saved!

01:00:22.107 --> 01:00:23.442
I can't take it no more.
Stop it!

01:00:23.526 --> 01:00:24.568
I can't take it!

01:00:24.652 --> 01:00:26.362
Hold on.
Now, wait a minute, man.

01:00:26.403 --> 01:00:27.780
Take your hands off me!

01:00:27.863 --> 01:00:29.532
This ain't right!

01:00:29.698 --> 01:00:32.076
Just let the people
hear the music.

01:00:32.409 --> 01:00:35.329
Y'all sitting here,
listenin' to this devil!

01:00:35.412 --> 01:00:38.541
You're just givin' your money
to Satan, that's what you're doin'.

01:00:38.624 --> 01:00:40.584
Hold on, y — you got a problem?

01:00:40.668 --> 01:00:42.253
Yeah, I got a problem!

01:00:42.336 --> 01:00:44.171
That's gospel you're singin'!

01:00:44.255 --> 01:00:46.340
You're turning
God's music into sex.

01:00:46.423 --> 01:00:48.425
You're making money off the Lord!

01:00:48.509 --> 01:00:51.345
Don't y'all smile at me!
All of y'all are in it, too!

01:00:51.428 --> 01:00:53.472
All of y'all are
going straight to hell!

01:00:53.556 --> 01:00:54.557
She's right.

01:00:56.267 --> 01:00:57.434
No, this here's wrong.

01:00:57.518 --> 01:00:58.727
The whole thing's wrong.

01:00:59.895 --> 01:01:01.730
It's okay. It's okay.
Let ... let him go.

01:01:02.898 --> 01:01:04.692
You got a right to believe
in what you believe.

01:01:04.733 --> 01:01:06.902
You can go
to hell by yourself!

01:01:06.986 --> 01:01:08.529
Boss, you want
to cancel the show?

01:01:08.612 --> 01:01:09.947
Uh, no. I'm not gonna
cancel the show.

01:01:10.030 --> 01:01:11.574
Just find me
a bari player by tomorrow.

01:01:11.657 --> 01:01:14.034
I just want to ask
the folks right now:

01:01:14.076 --> 01:01:17.079
If all of y'all want me to keep
playing, let me hear you say "Amen."

01:01:17.162 --> 01:01:19.164
Amen!

01:01:19.248 --> 01:01:21.041
And while you're at it,
find me a girl ...

01:01:21.083 --> 01:01:22.668
with church-training
that can sing ...

01:01:22.751 --> 01:01:23.919
but without the church attitude.

01:01:23.961 --> 01:01:25.045
All right.

01:01:25.087 --> 01:01:26.922
Let's go, y'all.
Keep it going, here we go ...

01:01:26.964 --> 01:01:28.591
Come on.

01:01:35.556 --> 01:01:37.558
♪ Let me tell you
'bout a girl I know ♪

01:01:38.309 --> 01:01:40.811
♪ She is my baby
and she lives next door ♪

01:01:45.649 --> 01:01:47.109
Ray, you got your watch?

01:01:47.151 --> 01:01:48.194
Yeah.

01:01:48.277 --> 01:01:51.906
Good. All right, baby,
your blue shirts are on top,

01:01:51.947 --> 01:01:55.409
the pants in between, and the
white shirts are on the bottom.

01:01:55.784 --> 01:01:58.454
Here's your glasses.
There you go.

01:02:00.122 --> 01:02:01.123
Bea.

01:02:01.624 --> 01:02:03.918
Why don't you come,
go on the road with us?

01:02:03.959 --> 01:02:06.086
Look, baby, what would
I do on the road?

01:02:06.128 --> 01:02:08.505
You'd do what I say you do,
that's what you're gonna do.

01:02:09.673 --> 01:02:13.469
I've been trying to get a female
voice in the band, anyway.

01:02:13.511 --> 01:02:16.347
Can't you just picture me
wobbling around on that stage,

01:02:16.430 --> 01:02:17.640
big as a house?

01:02:17.723 --> 01:02:19.725
Well, I can't picture you,
you know that.

01:02:19.808 --> 01:02:21.268
But I know what I can do.

01:02:22.978 --> 01:02:25.731
Come on, now. Don't start
nothing you can't finish.

01:02:25.814 --> 01:02:27.233
Jeff is waiting.

01:02:28.692 --> 01:02:30.903
You know I can't go
on the road with you,

01:02:30.986 --> 01:02:32.446
not with your baby inside me.

01:02:32.530 --> 01:02:33.572
Mmm-hmm.

01:02:33.656 --> 01:02:35.616
I'm gonna get your shaving kit.

01:02:36.617 --> 01:02:38.452
Uh, Bea,
I ... I got it.

01:02:39.078 --> 01:02:40.704
Bea, hold ... hold on.

01:02:45.125 --> 01:02:46.669
Bea, let me get it.

01:02:47.711 --> 01:02:50.297
How long you been
hiding this from me?

01:02:51.715 --> 01:02:52.716
Ray!

01:02:54.176 --> 01:02:55.511
I'm your wife!

01:02:55.594 --> 01:02:57.471
Bea, I ... I was just so
excited to see you.

01:02:57.555 --> 01:02:59.849
I forgot to leave it back there
with the band, that's all.

01:02:59.890 --> 01:03:01.225
Let me ... Let me get it.

01:03:01.308 --> 01:03:03.519
Oh, it's just a little medicine,
that's all, baby.

01:03:03.602 --> 01:03:05.020
That ain't medicine to nobody, Ray.

01:03:05.104 --> 01:03:06.480
Don't be lyin' to yourself.

01:03:06.564 --> 01:03:08.148
It ain't like I'm
dealing it, baby.

01:03:08.190 --> 01:03:09.692
I just use it
to get a little taste.

01:03:09.775 --> 01:03:11.527
You don't taste poison, Ray.
It kills you.

01:03:11.610 --> 01:03:12.653
Now, you got to stop.

01:03:12.736 --> 01:03:14.864
I ain't got to do
a goddamn thing!

01:03:16.448 --> 01:03:19.076
What about me?
What about your baby?

01:03:19.743 --> 01:03:20.744
Bea.

01:03:21.036 --> 01:03:23.205
It ain't like I'm new to this.

01:03:23.747 --> 01:03:26.417
If I felt like this was
jeopardizing my music, or you,

01:03:26.500 --> 01:03:27.877
or providing for that baby,

01:03:27.960 --> 01:03:30.087
I would stop in a minute.
But I know it won't.

01:03:30.170 --> 01:03:32.673
How do you know that, Ray?
How do ... How do you know that?

01:03:32.756 --> 01:03:35.217
You know what? You can talk till
you're blue in the face,

01:03:35.259 --> 01:03:36.969
it don't matter.
I'm not gonna stop.

01:03:37.052 --> 01:03:38.012
Then I'm comin' with you.

01:03:38.095 --> 01:03:39.013
No, no.

01:03:39.054 --> 01:03:40.139
Well, Ray, you just said ...

01:03:40.222 --> 01:03:41.849
No. No.
You know what it is, Bea.

01:03:41.891 --> 01:03:43.809
I ... I think
it's like you said.

01:03:44.226 --> 01:03:47.563
I don't think that the road
is a place for you and the baby.

01:03:50.149 --> 01:03:51.984
What are you saying to me, Ray?

01:03:52.067 --> 01:03:54.236
What I'm sayin' is
that when I get home,

01:03:54.320 --> 01:03:56.655
I hope that you're
here at my house.

01:03:58.407 --> 01:03:59.742
Your house?

01:04:04.330 --> 01:04:06.123
Jeff, come get this bag.

01:04:06.207 --> 01:04:07.708
All right, Ray.

01:04:09.835 --> 01:04:11.337
Hey, Della Bea.

01:04:17.343 --> 01:04:18.677
You all right?

01:04:42.326 --> 01:04:44.954
♪ It brings a tear ♪

01:04:45.120 --> 01:04:47.665
♪ to my eyes ♪

01:04:47.957 --> 01:04:49.500
♪ When I began ♪

01:04:50.251 --> 01:04:52.628
♪ to realize ♪

01:04:52.878 --> 01:04:54.630
That's good, thank you.

01:04:54.713 --> 01:04:56.090
How does she look?

01:04:56.131 --> 01:04:57.758
Very pretty. Brown skin.

01:04:57.925 --> 01:05:02.388
♪ I guess I'll drown
in my own tears ♪

01:05:02.471 --> 01:05:03.848
Yeah, yeah.

01:05:03.931 --> 01:05:06.809
Uh, oh, yeah, that's great.
I really dig your sound.

01:05:06.976 --> 01:05:08.686
Uh, what was your name again,
sweetheart?

01:05:08.769 --> 01:05:11.313
Oh, Mary Ann. Mary Ann Fisher.

01:05:11.438 --> 01:05:12.565
Mary Ann Fisher.

01:05:12.648 --> 01:05:14.108
Uh, Mary Ann, how would you feel ...

01:05:14.191 --> 01:05:16.652
if I asked you to sing a torch
song with a gospel feel to it?

01:05:17.862 --> 01:05:20.322
Well, Gospel's all about
love anyway, isn't it?

01:05:20.364 --> 01:05:21.365
Oh, yeah.

01:05:21.448 --> 01:05:24.451
Would it make you
feel like a sinner?

01:05:25.703 --> 01:05:28.289
Well, Mr. Charles,
I love the Lord, the Lord loves me.

01:05:28.330 --> 01:05:29.832
But I ain't no hypocrite.

