♪ Yes I believe ♪

01:37:17.921 --> 01:37:19.589
♪ I say I believe right now ♪

01:37:19.672 --> 01:37:22.050
♪ I believe ♪

01:37:22.133 --> 01:37:25.261
♪ Yes I believe ♪

01:37:25.887 --> 01:37:27.889
The sky's the limit, Ray.

01:37:28.056 --> 01:37:30.058
I got you a $5,000-a-night raise.

01:37:30.308 --> 01:37:32.185
They're gonna up you to 15 per.

01:37:32.310 --> 01:37:33.728
Rehearsal in 10 minutes, guys.

01:37:33.812 --> 01:37:35.563
Jeff, could you get
me some cigarettes?

01:37:36.231 --> 01:37:37.524
Okay, boss.

01:37:39.984 --> 01:37:41.402
15 per, huh?

01:37:41.486 --> 01:37:45.657
You know, Ray, your contract with
ATLANTIC is expiring in four months.

01:37:45.990 --> 01:37:46.991
Yeah.

01:37:47.075 --> 01:37:49.035
Yeah, I've got the contract with me.

01:37:49.160 --> 01:37:51.079
They're going to double my royalties.

01:37:51.162 --> 01:37:53.081
Before we jump back in that pond,

01:37:53.248 --> 01:37:55.416
I thought I'd find out
what else was out there.

01:37:55.500 --> 01:37:59.129
I had a very productive chat
with ABC-Paramount yesterday.

01:37:59.254 --> 01:38:01.172
ABC? Who told you to do that, huh?

01:38:01.256 --> 01:38:04.217
And you know, Atlantic is family,
just like the Shaw Agency.

01:38:04.300 --> 01:38:06.719
Ray, my job is to get you
the best deal possible.

01:38:07.429 --> 01:38:09.389
ABC is very interested.

01:38:09.431 --> 01:38:10.473
No.

01:38:13.101 --> 01:38:14.436
How interested?

01:38:15.311 --> 01:38:20.233
How about a $50,000 advance
each year for three years?

01:38:20.275 --> 01:38:22.360
You produce your own records.

01:38:22.777 --> 01:38:25.280
They'll deduct recording costs
and give you ...

01:38:25.655 --> 01:38:27.323
75 percent.

01:38:30.994 --> 01:38:32.787
Ahmet and Jerry are
flying in tonight,

01:38:32.829 --> 01:38:37.748
so will you put them off until
I can talk things out with ABC?

01:38:39.794 --> 01:38:42.297
Well, my mama said, ain't
nothing wrong with talking.

01:38:43.423 --> 01:38:44.424
Hey, enough of the formalities.

01:38:44.507 --> 01:38:46.426
Come on, let's go back
into the office, Ray.

01:38:46.509 --> 01:38:47.552
I hope I can call you Ray.

01:38:47.635 --> 01:38:49.095
I want you to be comfortable here.

01:38:49.179 --> 01:38:52.223
Because I'll tell you something,
everything is gonna be better at ABC.

01:38:52.307 --> 01:38:54.225
Moving from an indie label
to a major ...

01:38:54.309 --> 01:38:55.935
means you can sell
a lot more records,

01:38:55.977 --> 01:38:59.272
as well as attract much larger
crowds, both white and Negro.

01:38:59.355 --> 01:39:02.942
Yeah, but Mr. Clark, you know,
I've been at Atlantic for so long,

01:39:03.485 --> 01:39:07.781
I just want to give those guys a chance,
you know, to at least match the offer.

01:39:07.822 --> 01:39:10.116
Mm-hmm. Oh, certainly, certainly.

01:39:10.200 --> 01:39:11.701
But, uh, I doubt they'll be able to.

01:39:11.785 --> 01:39:13.745
We're giving you
a state-of-the-art deal here.

01:39:13.828 --> 01:39:17.207
Well, you know, since I'm producing my own
records, I was wondering if I could ...

01:39:17.290 --> 01:39:19.125
uh, own my masters, too.

01:39:26.674 --> 01:39:27.675
Well,

01:39:27.759 --> 01:39:29.969
Ray, we've ... we've never
done that before.

01:39:30.053 --> 01:39:32.097
No record company has.

01:39:32.222 --> 01:39:36.935
Well, I think I'm going to have to have it
that way for me to leave Atlantic Records.

01:39:45.777 --> 01:39:48.113
Ahmet believes
we're family here at Atlantic.

01:39:48.196 --> 01:39:50.240
I believe we're family
here at Atlantic.

01:39:50.323 --> 01:39:52.158
Obviously, you don't!

01:39:52.617 --> 01:39:54.160
Ahmet wouldn't believe it.

01:39:54.244 --> 01:39:55.787
You know what he said, Ray?

01:39:55.870 --> 01:39:57.831
He said you would never
turn your back on us.

01:39:57.914 --> 01:40:00.041
Never for a Schlockmeister
like Sam Clark!

01:40:01.209 --> 01:40:03.294
That's rich.
Sam Clark's a corporate slug,

01:40:03.378 --> 01:40:06.548
who wouldn't know the difference
between Earl Hines and Art Tatum!

01:40:12.887 --> 01:40:14.931
We let you grow here, Ray.

01:40:15.223 --> 01:40:18.893
And nobody's taking credit for
your talent, but we nourished it.

01:40:19.394 --> 01:40:21.354
We let you do your thing.

01:40:22.939 --> 01:40:25.150
God damn it!
We deserve better than this.

01:40:25.233 --> 01:40:27.277
You know what, don't think that
I don't appreciate ...

01:40:27.360 --> 01:40:29.154
everything you guys
have done here, Jerry.

01:40:29.237 --> 01:40:31.865
Ahmet, I'm very proud of the work
that we've done here together.

01:40:31.906 --> 01:40:35.160
But, Atlantic has done pretty good
money-wise on my records, haven't they?

01:40:35.243 --> 01:40:36.661
Yes, we've done very well, Ray.

01:40:36.744 --> 01:40:39.956
You ... you were the ones that taught
me that making a record is business,

01:40:40.039 --> 01:40:42.375
and find the best
business deal you can.

01:40:42.459 --> 01:40:45.712
Now, 75 cents of every dollar,
and owning my own masters ...

01:40:45.795 --> 01:40:47.922
is a pretty damn good deal.

01:40:48.465 --> 01:40:50.091
Can you match it?

01:40:51.050 --> 01:40:55.180
Ray, we would love to
match it, but we just can't.

01:40:56.514 --> 01:40:59.350
That's a better deal
than Sinatra gets.

01:41:02.270 --> 01:41:03.730
I'm very proud of you.

01:41:06.232 --> 01:41:09.819
Looks like those boys are going
to get a taste of country dumb.

01:41:09.903 --> 01:41:11.070
Yeah.

01:41:13.990 --> 01:41:15.325
He'll be all right, man.

01:41:16.493 --> 01:41:18.411
You guys always do find the best.

01:41:35.637 --> 01:41:37.138
♪ Georgia ♪

01:41:39.516 --> 01:41:41.601
♪ Georgia ♪

01:41:43.394 --> 01:41:46.231
♪ The whole day through ♪

01:41:46.397 --> 01:41:49.192
♪ The whole day through ♪

01:41:49.275 --> 01:41:51.402
♪ Just an old sweet song ♪

01:41:54.239 --> 01:41:57.700
♪ Keeps Georgia on my mind ♪

01:41:57.784 --> 01:42:02.413
♪ Georgia on my mind ♪

01:42:03.540 --> 01:42:05.834
♪ I said Georgia ♪

01:42:09.462 --> 01:42:11.798
♪ Georgia ♪

01:42:11.840 --> 01:42:13.633
Listen to that crap.

01:42:14.884 --> 01:42:18.221
Thought you said that ABC wasn't
going to force nothing on him.

01:42:18.471 --> 01:42:19.931
They didn't.

01:42:20.598 --> 01:42:22.308
It was Ray's idea.

01:42:24.394 --> 01:42:25.437
Something new.

01:42:25.520 --> 01:42:28.106
What are we then, Jeff?
Something old?

01:42:28.148 --> 01:42:31.818
Yeah, what about us?
We got to eat, too.

01:42:35.947 --> 01:42:40.869
♪ Other arms should
reach out to me ♪

01:42:43.329 --> 01:42:48.251
♪ Other eyes smile tenderly ♪

01:42:50.503 --> 01:42:55.467
♪ Still in the peaceful dreams
I see ♪

01:42:56.176 --> 01:43:02.137
♪ The road leads back to you ♪

01:43:08.897 --> 01:43:09.939
It's a hit record.

01:43:10.023 --> 01:43:11.566
What the hell is wrong with that?

01:43:11.649 --> 01:43:14.194
Critics say you've gone
middle-of-the-road.

01:43:14.277 --> 01:43:17.363
The orchestra, the choir,
The Perry Como Show, man?

01:43:17.447 --> 01:43:20.992
If I feel the music,
that means it's real.

01:43:21.075 --> 01:43:23.703
No, it ain't.
Ray Charles is a sellout.

01:43:23.787 --> 01:43:26.790
The blind Liberace, leaving those
Rocking Chair roots behind.

01:43:26.873 --> 01:43:27.832
Quincy Jones.

01:43:27.916 --> 01:43:29.793
Can we get a picture
of these two guys?

01:43:29.876 --> 01:43:31.711
- Six-nine!
- Hey, boy.

01:43:31.795 --> 01:43:34.214
Look, here, uh,
this interview is over.

01:43:34.297 --> 01:43:36.174
I'd love to
get you two together, man.

01:43:36.216 --> 01:43:37.634
S-some other time.

01:43:37.967 --> 01:43:40.595
Look at you. How's it going, man?
You look good.

01:43:40.678 --> 01:43:42.722
Let me look at you.
You look good, too.

01:43:42.806 --> 01:43:44.474
You hear what they're
saying about me?

01:43:44.557 --> 01:43:47.644
I just said that I ... I can't do it
no more. I've gone middle-of-the-road.

01:43:47.727 --> 01:43:49.145
So crank out another hit.

01:43:49.229 --> 01:43:50.355
Let me tell you something,

01:43:50.396 --> 01:43:52.857
it ain't easy
to keep on being greezy, kid.

01:43:53.316 --> 01:43:54.734
Where you blow in from?

01:43:55.944 --> 01:43:57.028
Paris.

01:43:57.112 --> 01:43:58.238
Bonjour.

01:43:58.279 --> 01:44:00.490
Yeah, man.
France is where it's at.

01:44:00.657 --> 01:44:02.742
Yeah, man. And all that stuff
you've been playing,

01:44:02.826 --> 01:44:05.245
man, it's just ...
it really feels out of sight.

01:44:05.286 --> 01:44:07.789
You know, we gotta
record something together.

01:44:07.872 --> 01:44:09.624
I mean, people will really dig it.

01:44:09.707 --> 01:44:11.584
So, where you going
after the Festival?

01:44:11.626 --> 01:44:15.421
Oh, I ... I go to D.C., Richmond,
uh, Virginia, Georgia.

01:44:15.505 --> 01:44:18.383
You know what, once you get the
record out there, you gotta sell it.

01:44:18.425 --> 01:44:19.884
The South, man?

01:44:21.094 --> 01:44:22.387
I'm not doing that no more.

01:44:22.429 --> 01:44:25.265
Hey, come on, kid, that's where
the money is, baby.

01:44:25.348 --> 01:44:27.892
You know, When I left Seattle
with Hamp,

01:44:27.976 --> 01:44:29.185
we went down there, man.

01:44:29.269 --> 01:44:31.855
And it felt like
I walked into a prison cell.

01:44:31.938 --> 01:44:35.567
You know, a black man
is a "boy" in Mississippi, Ray.

01:44:35.650 --> 01:44:37.569
Even if he's 80 years old.

01:44:40.822 --> 01:44:43.241
I'm never playing
to Jim Crow again. Ever.

01:44:43.283 --> 01:44:45.118
If that's what you feel, baby.

01:44:45.201 --> 01:44:48.872
I'm serious, Ray.
Man, we gotta do something.

01:44:50.582 --> 01:44:52.459
Well, you know,
what ... what the hell, man.

01:44:52.542 --> 01:44:55.920
You're just going to leave a lot
more money on the table for me.

01:44:56.463 --> 01:44:58.131
You're welcome to it, man.

01:45:13.229 --> 01:45:14.773
You ready to work?

01:45:14.856 --> 01:45:16.149
Work on what?

01:45:17.358 --> 01:45:19.235
Get over here, you gotta
help me with this.

01:45:19.319 --> 01:45:20.737
Percy just sent me some new music.

01:45:34.793 --> 01:45:37.045
You know what
they're saying about me?

01:45:37.128 --> 01:45:39.547
Said I've lost something, said
I've gone middle-of-the-road.

01:45:39.631 --> 01:45:41.883
They may as well say
the same thing about you.

01:45:41.966 --> 01:45:43.301
You were the soul of this band.

01:45:43.343 --> 01:45:45.804
Now every time you're around,
you're just drunk.

01:45:47.806 --> 01:45:49.307
Drunk soul of a blind junkie.

01:45:49.390 --> 01:45:51.142
What a lovely couple.

01:45:51.226 --> 01:45:53.603
Why don't you
just get out of here?

01:45:55.438 --> 01:45:57.440
I ain't drunk, Ray.

01:45:58.358 --> 01:45:59.692
I'm pregnant.

01:46:00.902 --> 01:46:03.655
Yeah, that's right.
I'm having your baby.

01:46:03.696 --> 01:46:06.533
You ain't really ...
You ... you can't do that.

01:46:06.991 --> 01:46:08.660
I'm gonna have to
talk to the doctor.

01:46:08.701 --> 01:46:09.869
You gotta get rid of it.

01:46:11.287 --> 01:46:13.123
My God!

01:46:13.248 --> 01:46:15.416
What, because
I'm not your precious Bea?

01:46:16.000 --> 01:46:18.211
I'm not good enough
to have this baby?

01:46:19.379 --> 01:46:21.965
You lay up
in my bed every night.

01:46:22.048 --> 01:46:23.258
My bed!

01:46:24.384 --> 01:46:26.052
I'm gonna have this baby, Ray.

01:46:29.264 --> 01:46:31.641
- No, Ray! No!
- Come on, come on. Come on, just listen.

01:46:31.724 --> 01:46:32.684
Just listen to me.

01:46:32.767 --> 01:46:34.102
You know
I care about you, baby.

01:46:34.185 --> 01:46:36.521
I won't let nothing happen to you.
I'll pay for everything.

01:46:36.563 --> 01:46:37.647
No!

01:46:37.730 --> 01:46:39.899
It's gonna cost you
more than money.

01:46:39.941 --> 01:46:42.944
I want you to leave her, Ray.
Come and be with our baby.

01:46:43.027 --> 01:46:46.531
You out of your damn mind. You knew
the rules when you got into this.

01:46:46.573 --> 01:46:48.950
You know goddamn well I ain't
gonna leave my family.

01:46:50.368 --> 01:46:52.036
Leave your family?

01:46:52.370 --> 01:46:54.873
You are a damn fool,
you know that?

01:46:55.623 --> 01:46:58.960
Between the dope
and the music and me,

01:46:59.043 --> 01:47:01.713
you already done left
your damn family!

01:47:02.213 --> 01:47:06.092
You know what the sad part about
it is, Ray, you don't even know it.

01:47:11.014 --> 01:47:12.515
You know what?

01:47:12.599 --> 01:47:16.102
From now on, it's strictly
business between you and me.

01:47:19.147 --> 01:47:21.900
Yeah, that's it. That's it.
Keep that anger.

